title: oriental broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli slaw and scallions. Add almonds and sunflower seeds. Break up noodles into bite size pieces in the bag. Separate out the two flavor packets and reserve for the dressing. Add broken noodles to slaw mixture.

title: piccalilli
directions: Wash and slice green tomatoes.	Add onions, red peppers and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain juices and chop through a meat grinder.
Add
pounds
brown
sugar.
Tie mixture of spices in bag.
Cook	spice
bag in piccalilli with 3/4 quarts vinegar for 1 hour.
Seal while hot.

title: brown gravy
directions: Brown flour in fat.
Add water and stir until boiling.
Season and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: brisket with marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well and rub into meat. Wrap tightly in heavy foil and refrigerate overnight. Unwrap. Place on grill for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning once. Remove from grill and wrap tightly in heavy duty foil. Bake at 250° for 4 to 6 hours. Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup.

Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches hard crack stage on candy thermometer (25 to 50 minutes). Remove from heat. Add food coloring and cinnamon oil. Stir carefully (mixture is hot). Sift powdered sugar into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Let set 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Crack with handle of butter knife.
Sift more powdered sugar on top.
Store in jars or Ziploc bags.

title: duffie's deer camp squirrel and gravy
directions: Cut
up
squirrels
(or
less
if you can't get that many), just
like
you
would
a	chicken
for frying.
Young squirrels preferred
but
an	old one will do.
It just takes longer to cook.
Soak dressed squirrel in salt water for about 30
minutes. Make
a
batter
with eggs, flour and milk.
Dip squirrel
in batter
and
fry in hot cooking oil until brown. Make a roux with flour and oil drippings from fry pan that you fried squirrel
in. Cook
roux just enough for it to be brown and thick.
Add water to roux and make a thin gravy.
Salt and pepper
to
taste.
Place squirrel in a large cooking pan such as a
bread
pan
and	pour gravy over the squirrel.
Place in oven and
turn
heat
up
until the gravy starts to boil, then turn
down
to
simmer
and	let simmer until the squirrel is tender.
This	may
take 2 to 3 hours.
If you are in the deer camp and
you
do
not have an oven, you can cook in a covered pan and
get
the
same
results. If	you
have an oven, make biscuits
for
soppin
of
the gravy. I guarantee this recipe will get the deer hunters attention.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix rice, soups and mushrooms in casserole dish.
Place browned chops on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°
for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Sprinkle grated cheese over cut-up potatoes.
Pour milk over and add salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Bake in oven with cover 1 hour at 425°.

title: vinegar
directions: It will be fit for use in a few days.
This is the recipe for cider vinegar which is sold in the country stores.

title: golden broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine soup, cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Stir into broccoli. Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 87 calories and 5 g fat per serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli well.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream, chopped celery, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli in a casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese (shredded) and potato chips.
Place in preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown the bacon and onion in skillet. Crumble bacon. Put in shaker to mix the vinegar, water and cornstarch.
Pour over bacon and onion and cook about 3 minutes. Add the sliced potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat and serve hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash
cucumbers;
slice
as
thin
as
possible (do not peel). Chop onions.
Add to cucumbers; cover with cold water. Add canning
salt.
Let stand 3 hours.	Drain.	Combine vinegar, sugar
and spices in a large cooking kettle.
Bring to a boil. Add
cucumbers.
Heat thoroughly; do not boil.
Pack in hot jars. Seal at once.
Hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with taco sauce.
Spread on a platter.
Put lettuce on top of cheese mixture.
Spread out evenly.
Do the same with the tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: zucchini-cheese casserole
directions: Wash and slice zucchini, steam 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Mix cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, egg and dill weed.
Spread over zucchini and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until top is brown and crispy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread pudding
directions: Spread butter on bread and put in 12-inch baking dish, beat eggs until creamy, add sugar and beat.
Add milk and flavoring, mix well.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle nutmeg and sugar over top to help brown.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: creole potatoes
directions: Simmer potatoes in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and add green pepper, onion and tomato juice.
Simmer 10 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste while simmering.
Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix together caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cook over hot water until melted.

title: no crust cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese with 3/4 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Add 1/2 teaspoon flavoring.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pie plate or pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon flavoring.
Pour mixture into cavity of cake.
Bake at 325° for additional 20 minutes.
Cool and chill. Top with fruit, if desired.

title: italian beef
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook until done, at least 3 1/2 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots and onion in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients.
Blend well. Pour dressing over cabbage and toss.
Chill several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove from bone and cut into small pieces.
Add noodles, soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole (1 large or 2 small) dishes; put crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Place rice in greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with combined vegetables and seasonings.

title: 20 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Wash rice, spread on bottom of buttered 10-inch iron frying pan.
Salt and pepper pork chops.
Place on top of rice.
Slice onion thin, place on top of chops.
Place green pepper rings on top of onions.
Take canned tomatoes, drain and pour over chops. Dissolve chicken bouillon cube in water; fill cup with juice drained from tomatoes, enough to make 1 cup.

title: cavatini
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of sausage, noodles, pepperoni, onion, green peppers, cheese and 1/2 of spaghetti sauce, remaining sausage, pepperoni, onion, green peppers, spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Use 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Whip the butter and 2 eggs; add cake mix.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: date squares
directions: Mix and press half mixture in pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Place foil on countertop to cool cookies.

title: zucchini in beer batter
directions: Let beer stand open at room temperature until flat, about 45 minutes.
In a bowl, mix together flour, cheese and spices.
Add olive oil, beaten egg yolks and beer.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg white.
Dip zucchini (sliced medium thick) in batter.
Fry in cooking oil which is already hot until golden brown.
Fry 2 to 5 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add flour and salt to yeast mixture and mix well.
Add shortening and work in with clean hands.
Shape into a ball.
Cover and let rise in a warm place. When nicely risen, pat into a greased pizza pan and add sauce and toppings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slowly saute onions in butter until soft and golden.
Sprinkle onions with flour; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in condensed beef broth, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
When soup is done, stir in Parmesan cheese.
Ladle soup into 6 individual, ovenproof bowls. Add croutons and sliced Swiss or Gruyere cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts and bubbles.
Serve at once.

title: pecan chip dip
directions: Saute pecans in oleo one minute.
Add onion.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add cheese; stir.
Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain
fruit
well
and mix.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt brown sugar, curry powder and margarine; pour over mixed fruit. Heat
in
a
oven for 30 minutes, being sure the fruit neither
burns
nor cooks too long.
Serve hot.
Serves 20.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add milk to corn.
Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and pepper.
Combine with milk mixture.
Add melted butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly until well blended. Drop by spoonfuls in deep fat.
Fry to a golden brown; drain hot.

title: just for kids: kellie's carrots
directions: Wash carrots.
Remove outer surface with vegetable parer. Place carrots on chopping board and cut in strips.
Run 1-inch of cold water into saucepan.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt.
Place pan over high heat and bring water to a boil.
Add carrot strips.
Cover with a lid and lower heat.
Cook about 15 minutes or until tender. Pierce with a fork to check tenderness.
Drain.
Empty carrots into a bowl.
Dot with plenty of butter.
Salt and pepper as you please.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake in greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan according to package instructions.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Then mix with pudding, 1 cream cheese.
Spread on cooled cake.
Strain pineapple and put on top of pudding mix on cake.
Put Cool Whip or Dream Whip on top.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: applettes
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Combine with apples and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Add walnuts and flavorings.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Pour into an 8 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar. Jonathan apples have the best flavor for this candy.

title: pickled green beans or pickled brussels sprouts
directions: Pack beans or Brussels sprouts into hot, sterilized, canning pint jars.
Remove seeds and trim top from cayenne peppers and add 1 pepper to each jar.
Add 2 whole garlic cloves and 1 head of dill to each jar.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Butter bread and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and drain sausage.
Spread over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Pour over all.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: white bread(rolls or 2 loaves)
directions: Add 1 teaspoon sugar and softened yeast in the 1/4 cup water. Add warm milk.
Add rest of sugar.
Stir in half of flour and beat well.
Cover and set in warm place until batter is bubbly and light.
Add salt, melted shortening and enough flour to make dough of desired stiffness.
Turn onto floured board and knead thoroughly until satiny and smooth.
Shape into 2 loaves or rolls; put in greased pans.
Set in warm place.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mediterranean beet salad
directions: Drain beets; dice and set aside.
In bowl, beat olive oil and lemon juice with whisk.
Add yogurt, garlic, salt and pepper; beat thoroughly.
Fold in beets.
Line serving dish with lettuce. Spoon beet mixture into bowl; scatter parsley over beets.

title: turkey or chicken crunch casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in undiluted soup and mayo.
Mix with the meat.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread crushed potato chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: raspberry mousse
directions: In a small saucepan, combine 1 package undrained raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Chill thoroughly.

title: apple fritters
directions: Select cooking apples.
Wash, core and slice about 1/2-inch thick.
Sift and mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg well and add to milk.
Add milk to flour mixture and stir until smooth.
Dip apples into batter.
Place in hot, well-greased skillet.
Add about 1 tablespoon water and cover skillet tightly.
Turn apples when tops are bubbly and the under sides are brown.
Add another spoonful of water.
Cover and cook until fritters are puffy and apples are done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and biscuit mix.
Add cheese in a mixing bowl. Mix well. Shape into cocktail meatballs.
Place in baking pan. Bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
May be made ahead and frozen.
Reheat and serve.

title: savory chicken nuggets
directions: In medium bowl, combine 2 teaspoons of Seasoning Mix and chicken pieces; stir until well coated.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour and remaining Seasoning Mix. Set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs and milk until well blended.
In a skillet or deep fryer, heat 3/4 inch oil to 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Butter, eggs and sour cream should be at room temperature.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla together.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine with shortening mixture. Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse to cool.
Heat tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato sauce in skillet.
Simmer to break up tomatoes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix pie filling, rhubarb and sugar; set stand for 10 minutes. Boil, stirring often, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add jello and mix until dissolved.
Put in jars and refrigerate or freeze.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour, sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Flour raisins, then add to batter with nuts and apples.
Batter will be thick.
Put in floured tube pan.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour, then test.
Use a caramel glaze while still warm.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Let dried beef set in hot water a little while to take some of the salt out.
Remove from water and pat dry with paper towels. Chop fine; mix all the ingredients together and form a ball.
Then roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: pink salad
directions: Blend milk, cherries and pineapple together.
Fold in Cool Whip and let chill.

title: perfect corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in bowl.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: picante dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate.
Spread sauce over cheese. Sprinkle the onions, green pepper and tomato over sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: lo-cal fruit delight
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, pudding and vanilla.
Add yogurt; fold in Cool Whip.
Keep cool.

title: homemade candy
directions: Put milk, sugar and butter into a saucepan on high until it will make a ball; add vanilla and nuts.
Cook about 5 more minutes or until makes a ball, then pour on a buttered plate and let cool.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender and mix well.
Then pour into 4 parfait glasses and put into refrigerator to chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, milk and oil; mix well.
Add water, eggs and pudding.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 40 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Combine nuts and dates; cover with sugar, cherries and green juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add beaten egg yolks and flour to nut and cherry mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: basic low-fat bran muffins(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball and press chopped walnuts over outside of ball.
Chill!
Serve on crackers.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add soup to dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: love joy lace cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients by hand.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Dough should be about quarter-sized pieces.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat until creamy the cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper; spread evenly into a 9-inch quiche dish.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onions and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake for an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with fresh vegetables and Twigs crackers.
Serves 12.

title: pork chops en casserole
directions: Pare apples. Core and cut in eighths.
Place in a casserole in layers alternately with sugar.
Pour hot milk over all and top with pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, then remove the cover and season with salt and pepper. Continue baking until chops are nicely browned on top.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add eggs, juice and liquors.
Beat on low speed 1/2 minute, then on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Scrape bowl frequently.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or in 2 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to rack and pour on glaze while cake is warm.

title: no roll pie pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use half pastry for bottom and half for top.
Put in favorite filling.
Bake at temperature that is recommended for filling.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Mix with liquid; drop from spoon into boiling stew.
Care should be taken to drop dough on a piece of meat or vegetable so that it may not be immersed in liquid.
Cover the kettle; steam for 12 minutes. Be sure the liquid is boiling the entire time; do not remove cover until the dumplings are cooked.
Good luck.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet. Add onions and mushrooms and saute until onions are clear.
Add meat and brown.
Add beef broth, salt, garlic powder and onion salt.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
In another bowl, stir flour into sour cream and blend well.
Reduce heat to low and add sour cream mixture.
Heat until thick and serve over cooked noodles.

title: microwave barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together the egg, milk, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Make into 18 small meatballs or 9 large meatballs.
Sprinkle with flour and paprika, mixed together.
Microwave, covered, 6 minutes on High; turn every 2 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Alternate layers of green beans and onion rings.
Save at least 1/3 can of onion rings.
Mix soup, onion powder and milk together.
Pour over green bean mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Then add rest of onion rings on top.
Bake additional 5 minutes or until brown.

title: fluffy strawberry squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Chill.
In large bowl, dissolved gelatin in boiling water; stir in condensed milk and strawberries with syrup. Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar; blend in remaining ingredients.
Use cookie press and press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes until set, but not brown.

title: tamale meat pie
directions: To Prepare Mush:
Cook cornmeal, water and salt in double boiler until thick.
Cover and let set until filling is ready.

title: verinikas(cheese pockets)
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and roll out as pie dough until very thin, about 1/8-inch.
Cut with a round 4-inch diameter cookie cutter (should make about 21).
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add any favorite seasonings to taste. Place a heaping teaspoonful of filling in center of cutout dough and fold over.
Seal carefully (spread a little water with finger around edge to aid in a good seal), forming a half circle.
After all pockets are made, drop a few at a time into a large kettle of rapidly boiling water for exactly 2 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon, draining as much moisture away as possible.
Place on waxed paper or Pam-sprayed jelly roll pan.
When all have been boiled and drained well (at this point they can be frozen and used later), fry carefully in Nucoa on both sides until browned and crisp.
Serve with Sour Cream Gravy and a green salad.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with sliced apples.

title: pralines
directions: Boil sugar, Karo, cream and margarine.
Cook until soft boil stage.
Add vanilla and beat.
When it loses shine, add pecans. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper sprayed with Pam.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix in order given and form into roll, 2 inches in diameter. Chill overnight.
Slice thinly and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Chicken:
Boil chicken until done with small amount of salt, remove bones and dice.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in an 8-inch square pan.
Add brown sugar and spices; mix well.
Arrange apple rings over brown sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons butter and cut to resemble coarse crumbs.
Add milk and vanilla; beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in egg yolk.
Beat egg white in small bowl until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour over apples.
Bake 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Loosen edges and invert onto serving plate.
Let stand 1 minute before removing pan.
Serve warm.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; separate eggs and add yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each egg yolk.
Add lemon rind and lemon juice, flour and salt; stir in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into the lemon mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350°; bake 35 minutes until done.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Place pineapple with juice and dry jello in saucepan; stir and heat for approximately 5 minutes.
Cut oranges in half and mix with cottage cheese.
Stir into pineapple mixture, then stir in Cool Whip.
Place in pan or dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: shrimp and broccoli quiche
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli; set aside.
Stir together beaten eggs, milk and green onions; stir in shrimp.
Toss together shredded Swiss cheese and flour; stir into egg mixture.
Stir in the broccoli.
Bake the pie shell in a 450° oven for 5 minutes until pastry is nearly done.
Remove pastry from oven and reduce oven temperature to 325°.
(If necessary, cover edge of crust to prevent overbrowning while baking.)

Pour mixture into the hot baked pie shell and bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean. Let quiche stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chili supreme
directions: Heat oil in pot and brown pieces of meat until it loses its red color.
Add all other ingredients except beans and simmer for 1 hour.
Check occasionally to make sure it does not stick to bottom.
About 15 minutes before serving, add drained beans.
If you like moist chili do not drain beans.
Heat and serve with hard crust buns.

title: chocolate cake with grand marnier
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Beat yolks and 1 cup sugar until smooth; stir in vanilla, Grand Marnier and lemon juice.
Blend in chocolate mixture.

title: french honey bread
directions: You will need a bread machine to bake.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables into medium pieces.
Cover with water in large soup pot.
Cook on high for 10 minutes.
Then turn to low and simmer until tender.
Eat anytime you feel hungry, as much as you wish, as often as you wish.
You will lose weight.

title: hot buttered shrimp(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in chafing dish. This may be heated on burner first. Should stay in chafing dish 45 minutes before serving.

title: tropical hash
directions: Place hash in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Combine pineapple juice with mashed banana, sugar and ginger in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Arrange split bananas and pineapple slices on top of hash.
Baste fruit with ginger glaze and pour remainder over hash.
Place under broiler until bananas are golden brown.

title: picante corn bread
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions together, pour off grease. Mix your cornbread together like you were going to fix corn bread, only pour half of the mix in bottom of a large grease skillet, pour your cooked hamburger meat over the corn bread mix, drain water off corn and pour over hamburger meat, pour picante sauce over this, grate lots of mild cheddar cheese over this, then pour the rest of you corn bread mix over this and cook till corn bread is done.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes in a large 11 x 15-inch greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Remove from oven and top with the following:

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in crock-pot (which has been greased with 2 tablespoons of butter).
Cut several thin slices of cheese and place on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Cook 3 hours and 15 minutes on slow.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Mix together well, then add dressing.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the ground beef; add onion soup mix, ginger, noodles and water.

title: autumn squash soup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place squash, carrots and onion in nonreactive pan.
Dot vegetables with butter.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of water over vegetables and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover pan tightly with foil and bake until tender, about 35 minutes.
Remove the pan from the oven and place vegetables and any liquid in a stockpot.
Stir in remaining 3 1/2 cups of broth, the mace, ginger, cayenne and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in sugar and cool.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture in saucepan.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: settler beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Brown bacon and onions; drain. Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Cook chicken until done.
Add tomato, water, onion, soup, salt, pepper and curry powder.
Stir and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the cornstarch; cook until desired thickness.
I serve this dish over rice and carrots and peas.

title: arroz con pollo(cuban chicken with rice)
directions: Precook the chicken with the cut up bell pepper and onions. Add the adobo and garlic. Cook the above in a pot until tender, or microwave for about 1 hour at half speed.
Be sure to stir frequently. Cook the rice with the Sazon and olives until almost done.
Add the chicken and cook 1/2 hour over slow heat, or microwave for about 15 to 20 minutes on full speed.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in 3-quart casserole dish.
Cook on high for 5 minutes.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook on high for 9 to 12 minutes or until mixture reaches hard ball (260°). Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Slowly pour mixture over egg whites.
Beat on high speed with electric beater.
Add vanilla. Beat until mixture holds its shape and begins to lose gloss.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger with salt, pepper and onion.
Boil and drain egg noodles.
Combine Cheddar cheese, soup and pizza sauce.
Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 15 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook 1 cup of raisins covered with water until plump, about 15 to 30 minutes.
Then in a separate bowl make a thickening with gelatin, salt, sugar and vinegar mixed with water.
Pour over raisins mixture.
Cook to desired thickness.
Add more sugar (to taste).
Pour into unbaked pie shell and top with dough.
Seal and flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Good with cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery and potato chips.

title: key limeade pie
directions: Thaw frozen juice.
Pour juice into a bowl.
Add condensed milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add green color and stir well.
Pour into pie crust and chill until firm.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Put in long 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese and pepper.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over last ingredients.
Place four or more slices of buttered French bread on top (enough slices buttered to cover casserole top).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch style potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Bake (in oven or microwave).
After fully cooked, cut lengthwise.
Scoop out insides, leaving 1/4 inch of potato to the shell.
Set shells aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 450° for 1 hour.
For the last 10 minutes, take out of the oven and put Cheddar cheese on top and melt.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Stir 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Mix in the flour, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt. Stir in the nuts. Roll into small balls.
Push with thumb.
Bake on ungreased pan 20 to 30 minutes at 300°. Frost with a dab of 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon flavoring and 1 tablespoon water with choice of food coloring.

title: candied apples
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in pot.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture spins a thread when tested in water. Place apples on sticks or heavy skewers.
Dip into syrup.
Twirl in air to cool.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates; pour boiling water over both. Combine sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Add date mixture, nuts and flour sifted with baking powder.
Blend together.
Turn into a greased, floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: On a large platter (with 1-inch edge).
Spread in layers: refried beans or guacamole, sour cream, cooked hamburger, Cheddar cheese, black olives and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with fresh vegetables, cut into small pieces.

title: easy deviled crab
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients thoroughly.
Place in clean clam shells, crab shells or 2-quart baking dish, sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs; dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 5 to 6 servings.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in a greased and floured 15 X 10 X 2 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together, except for the tomatoes. Drain juice off tomatoes; add to other ingredients.
Flash in blender.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook package of lasagna noodles separate.
Make layers with noodles and hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until melted.

title: buttered biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add milk and stir.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Put sherbet and ginger ale into punch bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Garnish with fresh mint.

title: korean cucumbers
directions: Soak cucumbers 15 minutes in salt water.
Squeeze out water. Add other 4 ingredients.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to box directions.
Pour over coconut and nuts.

title: quick and easy cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into a well-greased 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Blend ingredients except mushrooms.
Clean mushrooms.
Leave whole if small, cut in halves or quarter large ones.
Put mushrooms in container; pour over marinade (blended ingredients) and cover.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: salsa
directions: Mix well and refrigerate several hours.

title: my inspiration cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening for batter.
Add egg whites and mix well.
Add flour, sweet milk and vanilla; beat until smooth. Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cover bottom of pans with chopped pecans.
Pour 1/4 of batter over pecans in each pan; sprinkle grated chocolate on top of batter in each pan.
Carefully add remaining batter over chocolate in each pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix with next 7 ingredients.
Top with cheese and crumbled potato chips, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 2 minutes.
Good with hot curried fruit.

title: one wholesome salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil the zucchini and onion together for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix the cheese, carrots, sour cream and soup together.
Put one layer of stuffing mix in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch greased pan, one layer of zucchini and onion, one layer of cheese, sour cream and soup mix.
Repeat until gone. Top with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan that has a nonstick finish, or oiled pan (can be cooked in 2 loaf pans) for 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until done.

title: carrot pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a crust.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown and filling is firm.
Cool and top with cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 1 (8-inch) pie.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk and bring to a rolling boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir all the time as it burns very easily. Remove from heat; add vanilla, marshmallow cream and nuts (optional).
Beat well and pour in lightly buttered pan to cool, then cut in squares.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in margarine in skillet.
Add soups to rice and mushrooms.
Brown chicken pieces in a separate pan.
Place rice in oven-proof dish and top with chicken pieces.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Beat egg until light; add milk and melted butter.
Then add liquid mixture to flour, stirring well to make a smooth batter (use rotary beater).
Preheat griddle on large unit (grill or frypan) for 3 to 5 minutes and grease with 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon of shortening. Lower heat and bake cakes to a golden brown.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and stir good.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk (soda stirred in) and bananas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You can also bake in layers or loaf.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cut the cheese into chunks and put cheese and 1/4 cup butter in top of double boiler.
Melt until smooth.
Put vegetables into casserole.
Pour melted cheese sauce over vegetables and mix. Melt the other 1/4 cup butter.
Mix in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle the crumbs on top of the vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked nut bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, cool slightly.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Melt butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, corn syrup and butter together over low heat.
Pour over nuts and crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.
Enjoy!

title: cheesy broccoli-rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Add onion flakes to rice before cooking rice.
Add cream of mushroom soup to cooked rice.
Microwave broccoli using package instructions.
Add broccoli to rice mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with Cheez Whiz; cover.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: noodle bake
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix all together, reserving 1/4 cup of cheese for top.
Sprinkle over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
May be made 1 day ahead.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers (1 1/2 packages) to make crumbs.
Mix crumbs and butter for crust.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 15 minutes.

title: mother's holiday jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine buttermilk and jam.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and fruit.
Bake in three 9-inch greased cake pans for 30 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Melt margarine; add brown sugar and milk and boil slow 5 minutes.
Add crushed graham crackers, vanilla and walnuts.
Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Pour the cooked mixture over the crackers and top with more graham crackers. Frost with chocolate frosting.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lobster salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lobster and celery, in shaker. Add to lobster and celery, mixing as near to serving time as possible.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread slices and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown and drain sausage.
Cut links into round slices.
Spoon sausage over bread and sprinkle with the cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage, cheese and bread. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Add sugar and blend. Add egg yolk, then vanilla and blend together.
Use 1 package of rolls and stretch onto a cookie sheet.
Spread cream cheese filling on top of rolls.
Use other package of rolls for top (stretch them also).
Pinch sides together with fork.
Brush egg white on top with pastry brush.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown (time may vary with oven).

title: chocolate chip bar cookies
directions: Combine contents of both pouches with eggs and water.
Press dough into 2 ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Press coconut and/or chopped nuts into top of dough in each pan.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 19 minutes.
Serve plain or add topping.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and walnuts; blend well on medium speed of electric mixer. Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl sugar, flour and salt.
Bring to a boil oleo, water and cocoa.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, sour milk and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together in the large bowl.
Pour into greased, deep cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Melt oleo and put in oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over oleo. Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.

Arrange pineapple on sugar and oleo. Make cake substituting juice for part of liquid. Add enough water for specified amount to juice. Pour cake batter over pineapple and bake according to directions on box.
You may leave in pan or turn out on oblong platter.

title: cheddar dijon chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs and basil.
Spread one side of each chicken breast with mustard.
Coat chicken with bread crumbs, dip into egg and coat again with bread crumbs.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni per box directions. In skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken and cook 6 minutes on each side. Top rice with chicken, sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 300° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer cookies and bananas (one layer cookies, then one layer of bananas until you use all of your cookies).
Mix pudding and sour cream quickly (stir mixture just enough to mix it; do not let it get firm, you want it runny).
Quickly pour over cookie-banana layers.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours. Add Cool Whip on the top of your pudding either before or after refrigeration. This tastes like a "cooked from scratch" banana pudding.

title: beef-broccoli stir-fry(lo-fat)
directions: Trim all fat from steak; cut into 1/4-inch strips (easier if partially frozen).
Combine wine, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic powder and ginger in a bowl.
Stir well.
Add steak, tossing to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Combine water, honey and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; stir well and set aside.

title: do ahead dried beef casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Fold in sliced eggs.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple taffy salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Combine juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly until thickened; cool.
Fold in pineapple, Cool Whip, apples and peanuts.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: viv's hot buttered rum
directions: For Batter:
Combine ice cream, sugars and butter in medium saucepan.
Melt over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and margarine.
Add egg yolk and vanilla. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Roll into balls and top with pecan. Bake at 325°
for 10 minutes.

title: red coat rally punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine pineapple juice, sugar, lemonade and water.
Add ice cream and stir very well until most of ice cream is melted.
Serve at once.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Chill and serve with bite-size pieces of fresh fruit on skewers.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, sugar and
salt on low speed.
Stir in fruit and marshmallows; pour
into	mold.
Freeze
at
least
hours.
Ten minutes before
serving, unmold onto crisp greens.	Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well, scraping sides. Cover and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Spoon over buns or pasta.
May also be prepared on stove top, browning hamburger and adding rest of ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: lemon banana cream pie
directions: Squeeze juice from 2 lemons and mix with Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Stir in lemon rind and mix until thick.
Add bananas, sliced thin, and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip (about 2 cups).
Slice one banana to put on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate two or three hours.
Best if kept cool overnight.

title: microwave broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Cook cream cheese, Velveeta, Potato Buds and water for 5 minutes in microwave.
Stir and cook for another 5 minutes.
Add cooked broccoli.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Heat.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Combine noodles, soup, milk, tuna and cheese; add pepper to taste.
Heat in oven until mixture is well heated and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beefy bean burrito
directions: Put beans in 5 cups water to soak overnight.
Next day, drain and dry beans, add 5 cups of fresh water, vegetable oil and salt. Bring beans to a boil and continue to boil slowly for 1 hour. Drain beans, mash with fork.
Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat.
Add 1/2 package seasoning mix and 1/2 cup water.
Add beans. Stir and cook over low heat until heated.
Heat tortilla shells in a separate skillet, or pan on stove. Fill tortilla shell with beef mixture, grated cheese, chopped tomato, shredded lettuce and taco sauce.

title: bordelaise steak sauce
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter. Add wine and simmer until liquid is reduced to half.
Add gravy, lemon juice, parsley and seasonings. Serve on steak, London Broil or similar cuts.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix sugar, butter and hot water together.
Slowly add dry milk.
This makes 1 3/4 cups.
This is more than the amount in cans purchased in the store, so measure before using.

title: pork creole and rice
directions: In large pan, brown meat in hot oil.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to combine.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until rice is cooked and meat is tender.
Serve with green salad and rolls.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Sprinkle in black pepper to taste.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Chop fine the onions, pickles and tomatoes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.
This makes about 22 ounces of dressing.

title: ceviche de pescado(fish)
directions: Cut the fish into small cubes and cook in just enough water to barely cover.
Add salt to fish while cooking.
Slice onions, tomatoes and cucumbers very thin, placing in large mixing bowl. Add salt and the juice of the lemons.
Let the vegetables marinate while fish and juice cool.
When fish is cooled, add it to the vegetables (juice also).
Add cilantro to taste.
Serve with rice.
This will serve approximately 10 to 12 people.

title: herbed spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Combine spinach, egg, onion and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 16 balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until browned (18 to 20 minutes).

title: mixed fruit trifle
directions: Combine 1 3/4 cups milk, sugar and eggs in medium saucepan. Combine remaining 1/4 cup milk and cornstarch in a small bowl, stirring well. Add to milk mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in vanilla. Freeze 1 hour or until thoroughly chilled.

title: squash cheese casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash, combine with green pepper and onion in boiling water.
Cook until tender and drain.
Add margarine and sugar and stir until melted.
Combine milk, crumbled toast, 1 cup cheese, eggs and pepper sauce.
Add to squash and mix well.
Put into 4 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Pour melted butter into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add squash and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine egg, mayonnaise, green pepper, onion, pimentos and sugar.
Mix well and pour over squash.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 5 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini bobka
directions: Mix zucchini, cheese, eggs, oil, onion, bacon, salt and pepper, then mix in Bisquick.
Bake at 350° in ungreased baking dish (2-quart) for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: nacho skillet casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain well. Stir in sugar, oregano, chili powder, kidney beans, tomato sauce and corn.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle tortilla chips evenly over meat mixture; top with cheese.
Cover.
Simmer 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomato and shredded lettuce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Simmer sweet potatoes 20 minutes, drain.
Mash and add butter. Add other ingredients mix and pour into casserole dish.
Cover mixture with topping.

title: supper time casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Place in covered baking dish. Peel and slice potatoes and carrots. Add to meat and mix. Season to taste. Add soup and milk. Mix well. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: m&m krispies
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Stir in marshmallows, cooking until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat and stir in cereal, then candies.
Let cool in pan and then cut into squares.

title: orange cake
directions: Separate the egg yolk and white.
Beat the white of the egg until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to egg white until blended.
Set aside.
Mix the sifted flour with the salt.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolk until lemon colored (not under 3 minutes).
Add 1 cup sugar to egg yolk.
Beat until well blended.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavor.
Beat again until blended.
Add the flour alternately with the orange juice until well mixed.
Using over and under motion, add orange rind and egg white to mixture.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over cake.

title: goop(slime)
directions: Thicken water to the desired consistency with cornstarch. Cook until clear.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring to different bottles; let cool.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake as directed.

title: country meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add soup, pepper and stuffing mix.
Combine beef, veal and pork.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until no pink remains.
Drain.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix cut up chicken meat that has been cooked with onion, celery, salt and pepper, with the soups, broth and seasonings. Cover bottom of casserole with 2 cups Doritos.
Spread with 1/2 of chicken mixture, then 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers; end with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good with corn muffins, guacamole and Sangria.

title: beef roast with gravy
directions: Wash roast well and put in roasting pan.
Do not salt. Sprinkle instant soup over roast.
Add chicken soup and water which have been mixed.
Cover and bake at 350° until done, 2 to 3 hours depending on size of roast.
When done, the soup will be nice, brown gravy.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Place ham and cheese in breast and roll.
Secure with toothpicks.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: brunsviger(recipe from denmark)
directions: Add yeast to lukewarm milk; stir well.
Add butter, flour, sugar and salt.
Cover dough for 30 minutes.
Roll out into a square, approximately 15 inches.
Put in a pan and make an edge.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Heat butter and marshmallows in pan until melted.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour this over corn flakes and stir until corn flakes are well coated with marshmallow mixture.
Pour on a plate that has been greased with butter.
Shape into a wreath and sprinkle with colored sugar to decorate.

title: pasta primavera salad
directions: Mix pasta and vegetables in a large bowl.
Add dressing and mix lightly. Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, shortening and flour.
Set aside.
Add egg, sour milk and soda.
Pour batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan on top of dry ingredients and bake at 350° until done.
Do not grease pan.

title: spaghetti for 20
directions: Saute finely diced onion, pepper and garlic.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain oil.

title: apple bread
directions: Grease and flour 4 small bread tins.
Combine first 4 ingredients, mix well.
Add flour, spices and soda and mix well. Add apples and nuts.
Bake in 4 small tins 1 hour at 325° or 2 large tins 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: taco salad with beef
directions: Brown beef in oil; add taco mix and water and stir.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour warm over all other ingredients in large salad bowl; mix well and serve.
No other dressing needed. Serves 6 to 8.
Can serve with hot garlic bread or pizza.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Into a bowl sift together salt and flour.
Add milk, water, eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Beat the mixture until smooth.
Let the batter stand covered for at least 2 hours.

title: microwave seasoned potato wedges
directions: Mix salt, pepper, seasoning and oil in a bowl.
Cut your potato into 4 to 5 thin wedges.
Toss potatoes in spices and coat well.
Arrange on a microwave plate and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender. These make a good yet easy after school snack.

title: fresh kielbasa
directions: Cut pork into 2-inch pieces.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Put in refrigerator at least overnight, mixing once in a while.
Add a little more water if needed.
Put into casings.

title: chicken marengo a la lipton
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and brown chicken.
Remove chicken.
Stir in tomatoes, garlic and soup.
Return chicken to pan and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Boil spaghetti until done and pour tomato sauce over spaghetti.
Serve with chicken.
Serve immediately.
Can be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well together and let set 6 to 8 hours.
Will stay fresh for a long time.

title: chocolate syrup pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, chocolate syrup and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and milk gradually.
Add flavoring last.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sopaipillas(mexican bread - dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients except water.
Blend well.
Add water. Mix and roll very thin!
Cut into 2-inch squares which are then cut into triangles.
Quick fry in very hot oil (as you would doughnuts).
Under proper conditions, the sopaipillas will "puff" or rise immediately.
Fry only until light golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Best hot.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix.
Bake at 300° for 40 or 50 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cereal and pecans in 13 x 9 pan; set aside.	Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in 2-cup microwavable bowl.	(I used a 2-cup measuring cup because it made it easy to pour.)
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes; stir. Microwave 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes more or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda and pour over cereal mixture.
Stir evenly to coat.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheets to cool.
It took 2 large sheets.
Break into pieces after cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 10 cups.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Place margarine in 1 1/2-quart round casserole and set in moderate (350°) oven until melted. Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Spoon chicken mixture into center.
Bake about 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and yeast in a food processor. While flour mixture is turning, add hot water. Mix until dough ball is formed. Place in a greased bowl to rise. Roll or pat dough to fit pizza pan.

title: no bake yummies
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil; remove from stove. Add the oatmeal, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Take tablespoonful and drop on wax paper.
Let cool and set.

title: caramel fudge balls
directions: Chop 1/2 of walnuts to medium pieces and rest to fine pieces for coating.
Melt butter in pan and add sugars, salt and sour cream.
Cook to a boil and boil 5 minutes, covered.
Uncover and without stirring cook to 236°.
Remove and cool.
Add vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Shape into balls and roll in finely chopped walnuts.

title: sausage strata
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in a skillet.
Drain on paper towel. Place bread slices in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with cheese, top with sausage.
Combine milk, eggs and seasoning.
Beat well.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups supreme
directions: Flatten chicken breasts like cutlets, salt and pepper them. Layer each cutlet with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni or salami. Add 3 leaves basil, roll cutlets and secure with toothpicks.
Dust with flour and refrigerate about 2 hours.
Pan fry roll-ups in butter or other shortening for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, onion and sherry.
Cover and cook for 5 more minutes.
Good served over wild rice.
Adjust quantities to your needs.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes(12 servings)
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain. Mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and set in refrigerator.
May be used anytime in 2 weeks.
Place potatoes in greased casserole dish. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or heated through. Tastes like baked potato with sour cream and chives.

title: noodle kugel(16 to 18 portions)
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and rinse with cold water. Beat eggs and milk.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Mix with noodles and put in a greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top will begin to brown.
May be served hot or at room temperature.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Butcher may cut brisket if it is too large.
Place meat, water, cubes, 1 tablespoon salt, onions, carrots, celery and parsley into kettle; bring to a boil.
Remove scum, if desired.
Cover and simmer 4 hours or all day, if desired.
Cool overnight and remove congealed fat.
Bring to a boil again.
Add barley, pepper and 2 teaspoons salt.
Remove brisket; dice meat and return to soup. Simmer.
Serve with French or garlic bread and tossed salad.
A hearty winter meal.

title: sliced nut cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco well together.
Add eggs slowly, beating thoroughly.
Stir in nuts, then add flour, soda, salt and spices which have been sifted together.
After mixture has been well beaten, shape into rolls about 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready, slice as thin as you can. Bake at 375°.
Remove while warm.

title: rice delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Place macaroni in buttered baking dish.
Pour the other ingredients
over
macaroni;
do not stir.
Cover and place in refrigerator
to 8 hours or overnight.
When ready to bake, take a
spoon and go to the bottom of the casserole in several places without stirring.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cuckoo treats
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degree. In bowl, beat egg whites. Add syrup. Stir in cocoa powder, almond extract and cereal. Drop by teaspoon on nonstick cookie sheet. Bake for 30 minutes, until lightly browned. Remove from sheet immediately.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 8 paper or plastic cups. Freeze 3 hours.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first
ingredients;
set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing;
dredge
in
bread
crumbs
mixture.
Place chicken in 13
x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. (If chicken not
boned,
bake
for
45 minutes).
Contains 232 calories per serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs and flour until smooth.
Mix other ingredients.
Add pepper to taste.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°. Let stand few minutes before serving.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Cover beans with 2 to 3 inches of water.
Add ham bone, onions, bell pepper, bay leaves, garlic, pepper and Tabasco.
Cook slowly 2 to 3 hours.
Add salt after beans are tender.
Beans will make thick gravy.
Add sausage about 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil peeled, cut up eggplant until tender.
Drain in colander; mash.
While hot, add butter and 1/2 cup grated cheese plus chopped onion.
Toss this with beaten egg and dash of salt and pepper.
Put in shallow baking dish; cover with grated cheese and top with Pepperidge Farm herb dressing.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: garden party vegetables
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion with basil until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender and crisp, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: space cake
directions: In bowl,

blend together first 5 ingredients on low speed; then beat on high for 5 minutes. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes. Melt margarine and drizzle over hot cake. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar mixture on top.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut up and fry bacon; remove bacon from pan.
Add vinegar, sugar and water to grease in pan and bring to boil.
In bowl, put potatoes, bacon, green onions and celery.
Pour juice over potato mixture.
Serve hot.
(Some bacon grease may be removed if too much.)

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook onion and celery and add to hamburger. Mix in remaining ingredients, except for noodles.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake covered
1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add noodles on top and bake uncovered 20-30 minutes longer.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, but eliminate water.
Add liquid from mandarin oranges and then add cut up oranges.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: spanish hominy
directions: In a large skillet heat cooking oil.
Saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add hominy and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for approximately 45 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: banana pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine flour and sugar; stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir about 1 cup mixture into egg yolks.
Return all to saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Cool to room temperature stirring occasionally.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer 1/3 of pudding in 2-qt. bowl.
Top with half of the bananas.
Repeat layers topping with pudding. Sprinkle with nuts. Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Cut margarine in pats; place on bottom of baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, mayonnaise, soup, onion, pepper, cheese and broccoli together; mix well.
Pour in baking dish.
Crumble saltines; sprinkle over top of mixture in dish.
Bake about 1 hour.
Let stand about 20 minutes.

title: fried steak and gravy
directions: (This is good for any kind of steak.)
Pound it with pounder. Dip the steak in flour, salt and pepper well.
Heat skillet until hot and place pieces in pan (in oil or margarine).
Cook until blood appears on steak, then turn and cook on the other side until done.
(Onions and garlic powder may be added while frying.)

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain grease.
Stir in taco seasoning mix, tomato sauce and beans. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
On serving platter, place a layer of tortilla chips.
Spoon beef mixture on top.
Serve with remaining ingredients on the side.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand.
Cream oleo, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Add cooled oatmeal.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside to make topping.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and raisins.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend salad dressing mix into softened cream cheese. Gradually stir in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Use as a dip for carrots, celery, cucumber sticks, cauliflower, radishes, cherry tomatoes or zucchini slices.

title: fresh strawberry pie(dietetic)
directions: Prepare 1 envelope of Jell-O as directed on package.
Allow to semi-set.
Rinse and hull berries; place in baked pie shell.
Pour Jell-O over top.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped topping. Yield: 8 servings.

title: apple pork chops
directions: In medium saucepan, heat water and margarine to full boil. Remove from heat; add milk and potato flakes.
Stir to desired consistency.
Stir in cheese; set aside.

title: breakfast cereal cookies
directions: Cream Butter Buds, both sugars, Egg Beaters and vanilla with a hand mixer until smooth.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and baking powder.
Stir in oats, Triplets or Rice Krispies and Grape-Nuts.
Add raisins, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a baking sheet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, oats, onion, egg, parsley, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Shape mixture into 4 patties.
Fry on both sides in hot oil until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve in hamburger buns with lettuce and tomato or just as a patty.

title: pumpkin pan rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in the water.
Add the sugar, butter, salt, dry milk, pumpkin, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and ginger.

Beat well to blend, then gradually beat in about 4 cups of the flour to make a stiff dough. Turn dough out onto a floured board and knead until smooth (about 15 to 20 minutes), adding flour as needed to prevent sticking. Turn dough over in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in volume (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over kraut mixture.
Cover and set overnight.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flavorings and buttermilk; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; stir into creamed mixture.
Blend in chocolate.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place under tight-fitting cake cover while still hot. Leave covered until cool.

title: microwave peach jam
directions: Place peaches, lemon juice and pectin in 3-quart casserole. Stir well and cover.
Microwave on High until mixture is at a full rolling boil (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir.
Add sugar to mixture.
Stir well.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 7 to 9 minutes (stirring after 4 minutes) until mixture reaches full rolling boil, then time for 1 more minute after boiling.
Skim off foam and stir jam for about 5 minutes before ladling into prepared glasses.
Seal.

title: tuna-tofu spread
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients into a blender; mix on low speed until smooth, then set aside.
Drain the can of tuna.
Mix in chopped celery, minced onion and pickles.
Stir in tofu mixture; mix well.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend the mixture. Stir thoroughly before spreading on bread slices.

title: oh-so-good-cake
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, eggs, baking soda and brown sugar, then mix rest and sprinkle on cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add both sugars and margarine.
Stir until melted.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture. Mix well.
Add about half of the chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and rest of chips on top.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: tomato gravy
directions: After you fry pork chops, bacon, steak, etc., pour off as much grease as you can, leaving the flavorful drippings.
Add tomatoes to those drippings and stir well.
May need a little salt and pepper and if you did not have much flour left or were using bacon drippings, you may want to add a little flour to thicken, if you want it thick that is.

title: grandmother sam's cranberry orange relish
directions: Put half of orange slices and half of the cranberries in food processor.
Process until evenly chopped.
Repeat with remaining orange and cranberries.
Stir in sugar.
In a bowl, put the box of Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water. Stir well.
Refrigerate until it gets thick.
Mix the chopped cranberries and Jell-O. Stir well. Refrigerate until used.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl; pour into an 8-inch round, ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Invert immediately onto a plate.
Break into little pieces to serve.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk well.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir!
Pour sweetened peaches over batter.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: overnight crunch coffee cake
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight to bake fresh for breakfast. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Cream margarine, sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating well.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, walnuts, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over batter.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: special k bars
directions: Just
boil syrup and sugar;
add peanut butter and stir until well
mixed.
Press
into
an 11 x 13-inch greased pan. Melt chips in double boiler and spread on bars.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together and bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Stuff green chiles with cheese.
Place in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, side by side.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add garlic salt and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour over chiles.
Spread cream of chicken soup over top and add paprika for color.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
In a bowl, put egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Cook in microwave, stirring frequently until thick.
Stir in gelatin and lemon rind; let cool.
Beat egg whites stiff with 1/2 cup sugar and fold into egg yolk mixture.
Chill until set and top with 1 carton whipping cream that is sweetened with 1/4 cup sugar.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix in a separate bowl:

title: party punch
directions: Freeze pineapple and apple juice in their cans.
One hour before serving, set out cans at room temperature.
When ready to serve, place pineapple and apple juice in punch bowl and add the chilled ginger ale.
Stir to mix.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread onto platter.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes, olives and shredded cheese.
Pour 1 jar taco sauce or salsa over top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kuhlo's pork tenderloin marinade and sauce
directions: Mix all together and marinate tenderloin 4 to 8 hours. Cook on grill until done.

title: individual chicken dinners
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Take 4 pieces of heavy duty aluminum foil, 18 x 15-inches.
Place 1/4 chicken in center of each piece.

title: banana nut bread(one loaf)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients. Stir in bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage.
Melt margarine in dish.
Put 1/2 of crumbs into dish with melted margarine.
Add cabbage.
Sprinkle cheese over cabbage; top with rest of crumb mixture.
Mix milk, soup and mayonnaise in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over low heat and stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper. Cook, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in turkey or chicken broth and milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in turkey/chicken, vegetables and onion. Pour into bottom crust. Cover with top crust; seal edges. Cut several slits in top crust. Bake on cookie sheet 35 to 40 minutes at 425°. Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter, egg, flour and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 5 to 10 minutes. While cookies are warm, press a chocolate kiss (or star) into each cookie. Cool.

title: kat's crabby casserole
directions: Butter a small casserole and crumble rice into casserole. Stir in celery, almonds, cheese and onion.
Fold in mayonnaise gently.
May be topped with onion rings or almonds.
Bake at 375° until it smells irresistible.
Serve with salad for a fancy luncheon.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice cake around in half.
Mash strawberries.
Add sugar to taste.
On bottom layer, put strawberries, then put top layer of cake on.
Add strawberries to top layer.
Ice cake with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Cover with wax paper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan in 350° oven for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Add ingredients as in order in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoon on ungreased pans.
Bake 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: rice casserole
directions: Make up 2 serving-size rice; boil.
Add to ingredients.
Cook down 20 to 25 minutes.
Grate cheese on top.
Brown in oven.

title: jello topping
directions: Mix all together.
Do not put on jello until ready to serve.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Remove all skin from chicken; rinse and dry.
Dip in milk. Mix corn flake crumbs with rosemary and pepper.
Roll chicken pieces in seasoned crumbs.
Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken pieces in oiled baking pan lined with foil. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: main dish cabbage salad
directions: Mix together in bowl and blend with the following mixed-together items:

title: oyster dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add rice or moistened bread, parsley, seasonings, oysters and stock with giblets.
Mix and heat thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Yields stuffing for 10 pound turkey.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix 3 ounces cream cheese with cake mix, egg, water and oleo. Spread in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Put aside for later use (will be slightly stiff).
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs.
After mixing, spread on top of batter already in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top, if desired.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: *Add a little vinegar to milk.
This will sour it.

title: country steak
directions: Pound meat on wooden board with meat hammer; cut into servings.
Sprinkle with flour on both sides.
Brown meat on both sides in 1 tablespoon margarine and 1 tablespoon Crisco.
Sprinkle with onion, chopped fine.
Add pepper and salt.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Add more water, if necessary.
Yields 4 large servings.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Pour into floured cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add flour. Mix to form a soft dough. Chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix picante sauce and beans for bottom layer.
Then mix sour cream and cream cheese and taco seasonings for second layer.
Chop up and throw the rest of the stuff on top.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together until blended.
Add the pineapple and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake another 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blue ribbon lime pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in water. Add cucumber slices and let stand, weighted for 24 hours. Drain off excess water and wash 3 times. Return to jar or bucket and add cold water. Let stand 3 hours.

title: chicken paprikasu
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and cook in large skillet until chicken is done and onion is soft. Add the remaining ingredients to chicken mixture. Mix well and simmer while preparing Dumplings. Stir occasionally.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour on a greased 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed nuts on dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup powdered sugar on a linen towel. Loosen cake and turn out on towel.
Starting at narrow edge, roll up and cool.
Unroll cake, remove towel and spread cream cheese frosting.
Roll.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: black bean and mango salsa
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large glass bowl.
Whisk remaining ingredients in a smaller bowl, then add to large bowl. Combine and chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: elizabeth's fried okra and green tomatoes
directions: Okra should be cut for frying and green tomatoes diced. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to your taste.
Beat egg and pour over vegetables; mix until they are coated.
Then use self-rising buttermilk cornmeal mix and self-rising flour, about half and half.
Coat vegetables well.
Have oil in iron skillet and heat until hot.
Put in okra and tomatoes and slowly brown.
This may be done in deep oil or sauteed.
(I saute and then add oil as I think it is needed.
A few tablespoons of bacon grease adds much to the flavor.)

title: ice cream sandwiches
