directions: Cream butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy; add egg. Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Stir into butter mixture, mixing well.
Add oatmeal. Stir until well combined.
Roll cookie mixture into 12 to 14 equal balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls to 3 inch diameter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes until golden brown but still soft.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: mexican 7-layer dip
directions: Mix refried beans with half of the taco sauce.
This is the first layer.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Top with Fritos.

title: strawberry chantilly
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin and water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Chill until slightly thickened.
Thoroughly blend Cool Whip and drained strawberries into chilled pudding mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 cups.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Cake:
Sift cake mix into large mixer bowl.
Add 1 box of pudding, eggs, oil, soda and nuts.
On #1 speed, mix just enough to blend.
Then beat on #4 speed for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into smaller fluted or tube pan prepared for baking (greased and floured).
Do not use 12 cup pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick at 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out.
Ice when cool.

title: beef tips
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with cubed meat.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over a bed of rice.
Serves 4.

title: 60-minute yeast rolls
directions: Mix together scalded milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water; add to flour.
Mix together, then let raise 15 minutes.
Roll out dough on floured surface; cut and make Parker House rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheet (I just melt margarine on cookie sheet and dip rolls in it).
Let raise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and peel while they are warm.
Add margarine then mash well.
Beat eggs, add sugar, milk, and nutmeg; mix. Cook 15 - 20 minutes in a baking dish at 400 degrees.
Top with mini marshmallows.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Spread cheese in bottom of shallow dish (1 to 1 1/2-inch thick).
Spread chili sauce over cheese.
Put crab over chili sauce.
Serve with spreader and crackers.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Let boil. Boil spareribs until tender. Bake until brown.

title: baked turkey
directions: This is for any size turkey as long as you have a roaster pan large enough to hold it with the lid fitting tightly.
No foil cover.
It will work with a gas or electric stove if the oven registers the correct temperature.

title: ugly-duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.

title: chopstick tuna(chopstick chicken)
directions: Place tuna or chicken into mixing bowl.
Blend soup and water; add to tuna.
Add frozen green peas (unthawed), 1 cup of the noodles, tomato, celery and green onion.
Toss to mix lightly. Turn into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining noodles.
Cover and refrigerate, if desired, for baking later or place into 375° oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Garnish with cashews; serve hot.
Good served with fresh spinach salad and fluffy boiled or fried rice.

title: sausage stew
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in heavy skillet, stirring as needed. Add green beans, tomato sauce, water, onion, bay leaf, salt, garlic salt, pepper, thyme and bell peppers.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook with cover 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Remove bay leaf and serve in bowl.

title: bran bud muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds or flakes.
Add buttermilk and let cool.
Cream together sugar and margarine or butter.
Beat eggs and then add to bran mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake 22 minutes at 350°.
Batter will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: ham and cheese asparagus
directions: Lay one slice of ham on table.
Lay one slice of Swiss cheese over that.
Place one asparagus on top of that lengthwise.
Roll asparagus in the ham and cheese.
Do the same for each asparagus.

title: mexi coffee
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
To make, use 2 teaspoons mix to 8 ounces hot water.

title: cake mix brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 cake pan at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cook chicken.
Dice approximately 3/4 cup chicken, then add corn.
Stir flour and seasonings into melted butter.
Gradually stir in part of stock.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining stock and milk.
Cook over low heat about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add corn and chicken.
Serve hot.

title: corn souffle(hand me downs)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in deep baking dish (Corning Ware, etc.).
Cut butter in chunks and sprinkle on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese to top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from fire and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over 5 cups corn flakes. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper or cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.

title: celery salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine shortening and molasses.
Add egg.
Stir until well blended.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add alternately with the hot water to the molasses mixture.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: oven roasted asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 500 F.
Place asparagus in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Brush asparagus with olive oil.
Roast until tender but crisp.
Turn occasionally for even cooking and to avoid browning.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat Dream Whip according to the directions.
Add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Take graham cracker crumbs and mix with melted margarine.
Press into bottom of pan.
Pour cheese mixture over graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.
Put can of cherries on and enjoy.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, sugar & eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, and salt.
Mix well and then add the melted butter.
Lastly, add the nuts.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: pasta with pesto
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt, then add pasta.
Use wooden spoon to stir pasta until all is under water.
Boil rapidly until done.
Stir 2 tablespoons of hot pasta water and the cream into the pesto.
Drain pasta through a colander, then return to hot pan.
Stir in pesto and toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Simmer sugar and pineapple 10 minutes.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool.
Spread pudding over cake. Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with desired amount of coconut.

title: bananas in cream cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream bananas, sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Mix orange juice, vanilla and allspice.
Add sifted mixture all at once.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread with icing and garnish with sweetened banana chips.

title: cool cauliflower
directions: Trim and separate cauliflower into flowerets and cook in a large saucepan in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes, or until tender but still crisp.
Drain; let cool.
Combine in a small bowl the cauliflower, grated cheese and scallions.
Toss this mixture with the sauce.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine well, then add rhubarb and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread mixture into 2 greased loaf pans.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon melted butter; pour over loaves before baking.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour, or until pie looks done.

title: baked ham slice
directions: Select ham slice about 1-inch thick.
Place in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle with sugar mixed with spices
Add rest of ingredients and cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven at 350°. Baste.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine, confectioners sugar and salt together.
Spread on greased and floured round pizza pan.
Pierce with a fork to prevent air pockets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned icebox pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with beaten egg yolks.
Add condensed milk and beat mixture until it thickens.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Top with meringue made by beating 2 egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually beat in 3 tablespoons of sugar until it is dissolved.
Cover pie with plastic wrap and freeze until set.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Line bottom of pan and sides of a well-buttered 9 x 3/4-inch spring-form pan.

title: country apple prune cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs for 2 minutes at medium speed. Blend in apples. Combine dry ingredients. Gradually beat into egg mixture. Stir in prunes and nuts. Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack to cool.

title: corn souffle
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in milk in medium bowl.
Add corn, salt and sugar.
Stir well. Add beaten eggs, then butter.
Turn into buttered casserole and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, noodles and onion. Pour whipped dressing over to mix. Mix 2 hours or overnight before serving.
Add almonds and sunflower seeds just before serving.

title: hell fire dip
directions: Brown sausage, then drain.
Add cheese and melt over sausage. Serve warm with tortilla chips or dip size corn chips.

title: vegetable jello salad
directions: Beat first three ingredients.
Add salt and lemon juice or vinegar.
Add grated onion, cabbage, carrot and green pepper. Fruit may be used.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Turn into baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 30 minutes, stirring once after 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk jello
directions: Heat jello (dry) and pineapple together until jello dissolves. Let stand until jello thickens in refrigerator.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and pecans.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat first 6 ingredients until fluffy. At low speed, beat in next 4 ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until browned. Press a nut or chocolate kiss into cookies or you may press cookie with thumb and fill imprint with jam or jelly. Cool and store in airtight containers. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix pudding with milk; set aside.
Bake cake as directions say in 13 x 9-inch pan; let cool.
With a piece of thread divide cake is half, returning 1/2 to cake pan.
Support sides of pan to keep cake from sliding.
Cool cake.
Now layer cake, pudding, candy bars, Cool Whip, pudding, candy bars.
Place Cool Whip and candy bars on top.
This cake won two baking contests.

title: bran bread
directions: Heat 1 cup water.
Add bran and let set.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water, set aside.
In bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Add bran mixture, sugar and salt.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add yeast mix.
Use mixer until you can't keep adding flour.
Knead for 10 minutes on floured board.
Let rise.
Punch down.
Make into 2 loaves.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans (let rise).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 300° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole with corn flake topping
directions: Saute onion in butter, add soup and sour cream.
Grease casserole, layer 1/2 potatoes, 1/2 sour cream mix, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 soup.
Repeat.
Top with crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: venison saute
directions: Salt and pepper steaks or chops and place in pan with hot butter.
Cook 10 minutes, turning once.
Remove from pan.
Add remaining ingredients to pan and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add wine and cook 5 minutes longer.
Return meat to pan, turn to coat with sauce and simmer 5 minutes for rare, 7 minutes for medium. Serves 4.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple, Cool Whip and marshmallows. Sprinkle pudding over mixture.
Mix.
Add nuts. Serve chilled.

title: preacher's cake
directions: Mix together about 2 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini cheddar quiche
directions: Re-crimp pie shell in its pan, making high fluted edges, or transfer to 4 cup square baking pan.
Crimp edges.
Saute margarine over medium heat until tender.
Stir in zucchini, oregano, thyme, 1/4 teaspoon of the salt and half pepper.
Cook until zucchini is tender, stirring constantly, until most of liquid is evaporated.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and add remaining salt and pepper.
Add Parmesan and half and half.
Spoon zucchini mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Pour egg mixture over zucchini.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Then bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325° until center is done.
Cover with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.
Overlap cheese triangles over top of quiche the last 2 minutes of baking.
Let quiche stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger-cabbage rolls
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix in shredded cabbage; cook a few minutes longer until cabbage softens.
Salt and pepper to taste. Separate crescent dinner rolls, then stretch or roll out slightly to allow more room for filling.
Fill with mixture, roll up and seal edges.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ketchup.

title: dressing for fruit(from the golden lamb)
directions: Mix well.
Pour over slices of different kinds of fruit.
This is also good on macaroni salad.

title: kimberly cheese ball
directions: Cream together cheese and margarine.
Blend in dressing mix and 1/4 to 1/3 cup walnuts.
Roll into a ball in plastic wrap; chill well.

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Mix apple juice, cornstarch and Equal in a small saucepan. Heat to boiling and boil, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add margarine, maple extract and vanilla, stirring until margarine is melted.
Serve warm. Great substitute for diabetics to use on pancakes, waffles or even dip fresh apple slices in (as you would a caramel dip) and can be poured over boiled sweet potatoes.

title: punch
directions: Mix first three ingredients well until sugar is dissolved. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: icebox cookie cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin and cold water.
Cook according to package directions.
Cool about 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Add ice cream, stirring until melted.
Arrange cookies in the bottom of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour 1/3 pudding over cookies.
Place 12 cookies on top of pudding and 4 against long side of pan.
Make 3 layers this way.
Chill until firm.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses; mix well until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill, then shape into ball.
Roll it in chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: slick dumplings
directions: Sift together flour and salt. Pour boiling water into the flour and stir until well blended.
Place dough on floured board and roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch squares and drop into boiling broth.
Cook until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: cock-a-doodle stew
directions: Combine vegetables, seasonings and broth in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken and continue cooking 10 more minutes.
Remove and discard the bay leaf.
Mix together the flour and water and quickly add to the stew, stirring well.
Bring to a boil again and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Top with refrigerated biscuits and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger biscuit casserole
directions: Brown the chuck; drain. Add chili powder, salt and pepper. Add onion and optional pepper. Cook until onion is tender.
Add tomato sauce; simmer. Add 1/2 can water, if necessary.
Separate biscuits.
Pull apart to make 20 pieces.
Place 10 pieces on bottom of lightly greased pan or casserole dish.

Press together to form a crust. Remove hamburger mixture from heat. Mix together sour cream, egg and 3/4 cup grated cheese. Stir hamburger mixture. Pour mixture over biscuits in pan. Top with remaining biscuits, then top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° until golden brown. You may use a large can of tomato sauce and extra cheese to make this recipe even tastier.
You may easily double recipe by using a sheet cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: buttermilk doughnuts(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg together and set aside.
In a large mixer bowl thoroughly beat 3 eggs. Gradually add sugar while beating.
Add lemon or vanilla and oil. Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, a third at a time until well blended and smooth.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead dough lightly for 30 seconds, then roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry holes if you wish or put together and reroll to make more doughnuts.
Don't reroll a third time.
They get tough.
Heat oil to 360° to 370° or if your fryer is automatic fry when it's hot.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
While still hot, roll or shake in granulated or powdered sugar.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Note:
This recipe is still delicious using sugar-free pudding and light whipped topping to save a few calories.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: curry rice
directions: In a large skillet brown ground beef, onions, garlic, salt and pepper; drain off excess fat.
Return to heat and add curry powder, paprika, cayenne pepper and chili powder; stir well, blending seasonings with meat.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; rinse cans of tomato sauce with 1/2 can of water and pour into mixture.
If you like add additional seasonings to taste at this time.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Simmer curry mixture for 30 minutes; if mixture seems a little thick, add small amounts of water until desired consistency.
Serve over rice with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and put into casserole.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: classic rice salad
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly; chill.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with tomatoes and ripe olives.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until soft.
Mix in the sugars, using heavy beater.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add flour, soda and salt; continue beating until well mixed. Stir in the chocolate chips.

title: crazy cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Saute ground beef and add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° in covered casserole dish for 45 minutes. Take out of oven and top with Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: ham quiche
directions: Mix first four ingredients together, then add the rest.
Pour into baked pie crust and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and peanuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, peanut butter and whipped topping.
Spread on crust.
Mix puddings and milk.
Spread on mixture.
Top with whipped topping and peanuts.

title: moist date nut bread
directions: Place dates and baking soda in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over.
Let stand until cool.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream the eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add alternately, with flour, to date mixture.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: jiffy pineapple cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake Jiffy cake mix for 15 minutes. Combine second, third and fourth ingredients and put over baked first layer.
Let it sit for a while.
Spoon drained pineapple over Layer 2. Last, spoon on Cool Whip so it covers the pineapple.

title: lazy man's biscuits
directions: Mix with wooden spoon in medium mixing bowl.
Place in greased or paper-lined muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (12 to 15 minutes).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Add mayonnaise, grated cheese and chopped onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased casserole dish and cover with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake, uncovered, until cheese has melted, about 25 minutes, at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Roll into ball and then spread nuts on waxed paper and roll ball.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Place ingredients in a container with lid and shake well.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Combine noodles and next 6 ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Blend soup and mix; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish. Top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, in hot oven (425°) for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Add salt to sliced cucumbers and cover with boiling water. Let stand 4 days.
Drain off salt water and add alum to boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain well.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar (8 pints) and pickling spices. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cukes.
Let stand overnight.
Do this for 3 mornings.
On the fourth day, boil syrup and add the 2 cups sugar.
Pack cukes in jar.
Add syrup and seal.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix together in bowl and cool in refrigerator.

title: zucchini chili casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Cook zucchini in small amount of water until crisp, but tender; set aside.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, spread cooked rice in a layer and cover with chopped chilies.
Sprinkle half of cheese over chilies, then arrange zucchini slices over cheese.
Add tomato slices and sprinkle with salt.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken in egg/water mixture and brown in shortening. Pour off grease, then pour soy sauce mixture over wings.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Turn and baste, then bake 1/2 hour more. Great for party snacks or make lots for dinner!

title: stewed chicken and dumplings
directions: Place hen in kettle.
Cover with water.
Add celery, onion, salt, pepper, carrots, rosemary and bay leaf and simmer for 3 hours, until tender.
Remove chicken and strain stock.
Remove chicken from bones and cut up for serving with dumplings.

title: cold fudge sundae
directions: Cut the ingredients together; spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy fettucini alfredo
directions: In large saucepan, stir together the cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk over low heat until smooth.
Prepare noodles as directed on box; drain.
Add noodles to sauce; toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Stir yogurt.
Spoon onto layers of heavy-duty paper towels and spread to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cover with paper towels; let stand 5 minutes.
Scrap into a bowl using a rubber spatula.
Stir in mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except peas and mayonnaise.
Stir gently, then add peas and mayonnaise.
Stir gently.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Serves 8.

title: microwave clam chowder
directions: Place bacon in 3-quart casserole.

Cover and microwave on High 3 minutes. Drain all but 2 tablespoons fat. Add potatoes, onion, celery and reserved clam liquid. Cover and microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once.
Combine flour and 1/4 cup milk. Add flour mixture, remaining milk, salt and pepper to casserole.
Do not cover.
Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes or until heated through.

title: 7 cup cookies(servings:  4)
directions: Blend sugar, oleo, egg, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
By hand, add dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour or overnight. Shape dough into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, salt, flaovring and eggs; add alternately sifted dry ingredients and milk.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 375° oven; cool and put layers together with Pineapple Filling.

title: stickers
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil.
Add 4 packages of gelatin.
Reduce heat to low and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add peppermint extract.
Brush solution on the back side of pictures from magazines, drawings, etc.
Let dry.
Trim to desired shape and size.
Lick and stick.
Store remainder in an airtight jar.
Keeps months.
Mixture will solidify.
To use again, warm in a pan of hot water.

title: red cabbage
directions: In a 2-quart covered saucepan, melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir lightly.
Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cabbage is just tender.

title: italian icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick; let cool.
Cream margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat together, the more you beat, the better it is.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk or chicken stock, mushroom stock, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and Accent.
Stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 3 cups sauce.

title: country fair bread
directions: Pour scalded milk over butter or margarine, salt and sugar; cool.
Dissolve yeast according to package instructions.
Add yeast and eggs to cooled milk mixture in large mixing bowl.
Add flour gradually mixing well.
Use only as much flour as necessary for a light, tender dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; turn onto floured surface.
Shape into 3 loaves.
Place in 8-inch loaf pans. Cover and let rise until dough tops pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water, adding 2 cups of cold water.
Add crushed pineapple and pour into shallow pan or dish (8 x 12 inch).
Add bananas to jello and top with miniature marshmallows.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn meal and flour.
Cream together sugar mixture and butter.
Add milk to egg yolks; beat together.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until solid (25 to 35 minutes).

title: cabbage and nut salad
directions: Shred cabbage and cut nuts fine.
Cube apples.
Salt and sweeten to taste.
Mix with salad dressing.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Soak rice in water 1 hour.
Add beef.
Mix rice, onion, egg, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper and add to rice/beef mixture.
Put in covered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: salmon chowder
directions: In a covered pot boil potatoes, carrots and onions in water for 20 minutes.
Add bacon and boil 10 more minutes. Add peppers and boil 10 more minutes.
Add salmon and reduce heat to low. Cook 20 minutes.
Add corn, butter, and salt and continue to simmer until well-blended and heated through.
Do not boil.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Bring frozen peas to a boil; drain.
In a large bowl, place lettuce, pepper, celery and peas.
(You may add anything you want, such as onions, cauliflower or broccoli.)
Spread mayonnaise evenly on top of peas.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Top with bacon bits just before serving.

title: virginia's super duper country potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes while hot.
Don't worry if they become somewhat mashed.
Blend all ingredients with mayonnaise as desired.

title: jeanette's bubble bread
directions: Grease 1 Bundt or tube pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Break off pieces of dough about the size of a walnut.
Roll into balls, dip in melted margarine, then sugar mixture and nuts. Place balls in pan around the circle.
Cover with wax paper and put in warming oven until it raises to the top.
Mix remaining melted margarine and sugar mixture and pour over raised dough. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Take from oven and place upside down on dinner plate.

title: eggplant "sandwich" casserole*
directions: Wash and slice eggplant 1/4 inch thick (unpeeled).
Make sandwich style a slice of eggplant, meat mixture patty and another slice of eggplant.
Patties made of beef, onion, Parmesan cheese, pepper, m.s.g., oregano, salt and eggs.
Brown both sides of your eggplant "sandwich" in small amount of fat, placing browned eggplant sandwiches into casserole dish, fitting as close together as you can.
Mix tomato sauce and 1 can water, salt, pepper, oregano (to taste) and pour over "sandwiches."
Place Swiss or Mozzarella cheese slices on top and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil beet until done. Cool and peel. Set aside. Bring all other ingredients to a boil. Add beats and boil for about 10 minutes. Pack in sterilized jar and seal.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix these ingredients well and place in a lightly greased baking dish.

title: candy s'mores
directions: Place cake slices on ungreased baking sheet.
Place 4 sections of candy on each slice.
Arrange marshmallows on candy.
Bake at 350° until candy melts and marshmallows are puffed and brown.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Take cupcake cups and cut down to 1 1/2-inches tall.
Melt chocolate and 1/2 cup peanut butter in double broiler.
Take 1 cup peanut butter and put in Pyrex cup in pan of water until peanut butter is pourable.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Whip the cream cheese,
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in a greased dish 30 minutes at 350°

title: frito bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Marinate in French dressing 1 to 2 hours or longer.
Place lettuce, tomatoes and onion in a large salad bowl.
Pour beans and dressing over vegetables.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with Fritos.

title: caramel pecan sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to a boil and stir occasionally.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Cool slightly to thicken.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat cider, sugar and fruit juices (undiluted) in kettle.
Tie cloves and allspice in a small cheesecloth bag.
Add to cider with nutmeg.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag. Serve hot in mugs with a cinnamon stick in each mug.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together over medium heat. Serve!

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan; cool. Cut in squares.
Very good.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Put sausage in covered pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Drain grease off sausage.
Put peppers over sausage; add stewed tomatoes and sauce.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: divinity pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, crackers and nuts.
Cook 30 minutes at 325° in glass pan.
Cool.
Add a layer of strawberries. Top with Dream Whip and coconut.

title: chicken dumplins
directions: Cook chicken with water to cover.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from broth when done.
Let cool and debone.
Mix flour, salt and ice water into ball; divide into 2 balls.
Roll very thin and cut into 1-inch strips.
Pinch off 1-inch pieces.
Drop into rolling broth.
Stir only with fork.
Cut heat down to simmer. Cover and cook on very low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.
Use desired amount of chicken.
Remaining chicken is great for chicken salad.

title: basic stir-fried chicken
directions: Skin and bone chicken, then cut into small chunks.
Mince ginger root and green onion, then combine with cornstarch, sherry and water.
Add to chicken and toss to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Meanwhile, slice vegetables.
Heat oil.
Add chicken and stir-fry until begins to brown (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove from pan.
Add vegetables and stir-fry to coat with oil (1 to 2 minutes).
Sprinkle with soy sauce and sugar. Stir in chicken broth and heat quickly, then simmer, covered, until vegetables are nearly done.
Return chicken; stir to reheat and blend flavors (about 1/2 minute).
Serve at once.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: The night before, drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine pineapple and marshmallows and refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix margarine and crushed corn flakes.
Place half of mixture in greased casserole.
Spread cabbage and onion over mixture.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over cabbage. Spread grated cheese over soup mixture.
Spread remaining crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef and onions until juices evaporate.
Add tomatoes and next 8 ingredients.
Heat until boiling, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring mixture occasionally.
Spoon off any fat on top of sauce.
(Cook noodles.)

title: oven grilled ribs
directions: Rub ribs on both sides with salt, pepper, ginger and rosemary. Brush sparingly with soy sauce.
Place ribs, fatty side up, on an ovenproof plate or pan.
Grill in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, depending on thickness of ribs.
Check for doneness by piercing with a fork.
Remove ribs from oven.
Wrap in foil.
Keep warm.
Add hot water to pan.
Scrape up brownings.
Strain juices into a saucepan.
Heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cut ribs into even pieces.
Serve with pan juices.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, applesauce and eggs as usual; mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Grease tube pan and dust with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put cake mixture, then cinnamon and sugar, (I put raisins) and nuts; also cake mixture, cinnamon and sugar, nuts (almonds or walnuts) and cake mixture.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Put glaze on top if you want.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Cut around sides and turn out top side up.

title: zesty red potatoes
directions: Slice potato halves thinly and arrange with onion in bottom of ungreased baking dish.
Mix butter, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Drizzle over potatoes and onions.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with whole grahams.
In large bowl, combine pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half over grahams.
Top with whole grahams, another layer.
Spread with remaining pudding. Add another whole layer of grahams.
In medium bowl, combine melted chocolate with butter, corn syrup, vanilla and 3 tablespoons of milk.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over crackers.
Cover with plastic.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: jew bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add flour and remaining ingredients (except xxx sugar).
Spread thinly on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot. When cooled, cut in squares.
These easy to make bars are light and delicious.

title: elephant ears
directions: Heat small amount of oil in frypan.
Place 1 tortilla; fry until slightly cooked and flip and cook other side.
Remove from oil and place on paper towel.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cook the rest.

title: baked chicken
directions: Batter chicken breasts and place in a baking dish.
Combine soups and wine and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in salt water until tender; drain.
Stir the remaining ingredients together and pour mixture over the cooked cauliflower.
Simmer; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into cups and add a hunk of butter.

title: mom's hiya somen sauce
directions: Boil ingredients together.
Serve with boiled somen noodles and garnish with kamaboko, green onions and sliced, fried eggs.

title: barbecued chicken wings(serves 4)
directions: Cut off and discard chicken wing tips.
Arrange chicken and lemon alternately in rectangular 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch dish.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 6 minutes, until juices run clear; drain.
Keep warm. Pour favorite barbecue sauce over chicken.
Microwave uncovered 3 to 4 minutes or until sauce is hot.
May double for large crowd.

title: easy, easy, easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool. I divide the batter and put pecans and pecan flavoring, coconut and coconut flavoring, orange or lemon flavoring, chocolate chips, peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
I use a teaspoonful of dough and flatten with a fork.
These are so easy to make.

title: julie's eggs portugal
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer sausage, bread and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine milk, eggs and mustard in bowl; mix well.
Spread over cheese.
Blend soup and wine in small bowl.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: creamed chicken with mushrooms
directions: Heat
milk
in	top
of
double boiler.
Add the cut up chicken
and
allow
to
heat through.
Brown the mushrooms in frying
pan
using 1 teaspoon butter.
Pour this into the milk and chicken
and
allow
to
simmer
until
the flavor of the mushrooms
goes
through the milk.	Serve on a piece of toast, garnish
with
few strips of pimento and a sprinkle of nutmeg. Exchanges:	3 meat, 1 milk, 1 vegetable, 1 fat, 1 bread.

title: artichoke soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until soft.
Add flour and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Add chicken stock, celery soup, milk, parsley, curry powder and allspice.
In blender or food processor, chop artichoke hearts; add half to soup and cook for 5 minutes on medium heat. Puree soup mixture in blender or processor 1/2 at a time.
Return to saucepan and add half and half or cream; add salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce to taste and remaining chopped artichokes.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Refrigerate and serve cold. Makes 8 cups.

title: gram's jello
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water. Add Jell-O and vinegar, stirring well.
(I use a wire whisk.)
Add remaining ingredients and chill until set.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend to moisten; then beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour about 3/4 of batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Add 3/4 cup chocolate syrup to remaining batter.
Mix well.
Pour over batter in pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour, or until done.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: orange stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate to set.

title: fast harvard beets
directions: Drain beets and save juice.
Combine beet juice and water to make 1 cup liquid.
In a 1-quart glass bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir in beet liquid.
Cook for 3 minutes in microwave.
Add beets; stir and cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: scotch bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add nuts and mix well.
Melt shortening in saucepan; remove from heat. Add egg and vanilla and blend, then add flour mixture, a small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pans, then cut into bars.
Makes about 2 dozen bars.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Bring to
full rolling boil, stirring constantly .
Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch well-greased pan; cool.

title: sara's sugar cookies
directions: Mix and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut in shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and broccoli.
Lay broccoli in large casserole dish, sprayed with Pam. Mix other ingredients and pour over the broccoli.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and brown.

title: rhubarb kuchen
directions: Use same crust as for Apple Kuchen.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Mix soups and broth; bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken (can add 1 can of peas and carrots).

title: noel chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish skin side down.
Mix onion, cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, sour cream and sherry and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute beef, squash, onions and seasonings in skillet until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Stir frequently.
Add chilies, rice, sour cream and 1 cup cheese.
Pour into 2-pint casserole dish.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Stir in cheese and heat thoroughly.
If desired, substitute a 16 ounce bag of frozen vegetables.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Mix well and slowly stir in beet juice; blend to a smooth mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add butter and beets, stirring well to coat beets. Keep warm for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Add boiling water last, beating as you pour it in.
Put in oven at once.
(This is a thin batter.)
Bake at 350° until cake pulls from sides of pan. Makes 4 layers or a large sheet cake.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Add all ingredients and cook until it thickens.
Before sealing, add 2 teaspoons turmeric to cooked relish.

title: apple cheese bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and ginger together.
Add 1/3 of dry ingredients to egg mixture; stir in apples, cheese and pecans.
Add remaining dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into well-buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and cool on wire rack.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together flour, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and cold water.
Dip chicken in batter.
Deep Fry 350° until golden brown.

title: turkey balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine bread, celery, 1/2 cup walnuts, onion, salt, poultry seasoning, pepper and turkey.
Add 1/2 cup melted butter and enough broth to moisten.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in greased shallow pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until crisp.
About 10 minutes before serving, put walnuts (3 tablespoons) in small shallow pan.
Dot with 1 teaspoon butter and toast in oven with turkey balls, stirring once.
Serve balls with gravy; garnish with walnuts.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Fold in other ingredients and chill.

title: hungarian broilers
directions: Brown onions and garlic in butter; remove from skillet.
Add chicken and brown.
Put chicken in covered dish.
Return onions and garlic to skillet.
Add paste and broth; bring to boil and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cholesterol-free sausages with eggs
directions: Day ahead, rinse garbanzo beans in running cold water and discard any stones or shriveled beans.
In 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, heat garbanzo beans, salt and 3 cups water to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain garbanzo beans, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; mash.
(Add milk, salt, pepper and oleo.) Take 2 sticks oleo and chopped onion and simmer until tender.
Add 1/3 cup onion/butter mixture to mashed potatoes.
Add Cheddar cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Cook noodles.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Mix brown sugar and white sugar thoroughly.
Add syrup, milk, butter and salt.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cool to room temperature.
Beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Add nuts and pour into buttered pans.

title: lemonade
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add juices.
Stir in cold water to make 1 gallon.
Add several slices lemon to float on top.

title: rolled chicken washington
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Blend in flour.
Stir in cream. Add salt and cayenne; cook, stirring, until mixture is very thick.
Stir in cheese until it melts.
Turn onto pie plate, cover and chill 1 hour.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Pound out chicken breasts (boned side up between plastic wrap) from center with wood mallet to form cutlets 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle meat with salt.
Place piece of cheese on top. Tucking in sides of meat, roll as jelly roll.
Press to seal well.
Dust with flour.
Dip in eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Fry rolls in hot oil for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Bake in shallow dish at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Sift flour with soda.
Measure 4 cups All-Bran into 6-quart bowl.
Mix in boiling water, then add eggs, oil, sugar and part of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Continue adding buttermilk and rest of flour; beat.
Add 2 cups All-Bran and raisins.
Once all ingredients are mixed in, do not stir again.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out dry.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes before removing from pan.

title: great-grandma atchley's jumbles
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix.
Slowly add flour and nutmeg.
Make into small balls.
Roll gently in hands.
Space apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except triangle thins.
Line casserole with the thins.
Add salad mixture.
Top with remaining thins and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat
soup.
Soften
gelatin
in the 1/2 cup cold water and pour in the heated soup.
When cool, add all other ingredients. Pour into dish and refrigerate until set.

title: wine dressing
directions: Stir it up or shake it.
Drink a glass of wine while you're doing this and the whole meal improves.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage until leaves are flexible.
Cook rice.
Mix rice and raw ground beef together.
Add diced onions.
Take leaves from cabbage head and roll the mixture into the leaves.
Roll on the vein of leaf; tuck the flexible ends in.
Put in roasting pan; cover with tomato soup and kraut (mix water with tomato soup). Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake according to directions. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of the butter into pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In a saucepan, melt caramels, butter and milk over low heat until caramels are melted.
Pour caramel mixture over baked cake.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans. Pour remaining cake batter over this mixture and return to oven and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Put all in blender and blend.
Makes about 1 1/2 pints.
Keep well refrigerated.
Use as needed on shredded cabbage, a little chopped onion and a little shredded carrot.

title: pizza spaghetti bake
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Layer spaghetti, sauces, pepperoni and cheeses (ending with cheese on top).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salt-free meat balls
directions: Crumble bread; cover with sweet milk.
When soaked, add egg and beef, then mix in onion and spices.
Mix together well and form into balls (golf ball size).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve on rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and season with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.
Thin soup with milk or white wine.
Mix until smooth and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
Preparation Time:
20 minutes.

title: lima beans and sour cream
directions: Cook beans as to package directions.
Drain.
Melt butter and cook onion for one minute over low heat.
Mix all ingredients. Heat mixture, but do not boil.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Thaw pastry sheets about 20 minutes.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Saute in butter on both sides about 2 to 3 minutes; drain and cool.
Unfold sheets; cut into 4 squares.
On lightly floured surface, roll out pastry large enough to enclose chicken. Place chicken in center of pastry; top with a cheese and ham slice.
Wrap around chicken and pinch edges.
Brush top of pastry with an egg beaten with 1 teaspoon of water.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: In a soup pot, brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes and simmer.
Add other undrained ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Mix ingredients in blender and pour into mold.
Freeze.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan, melt butter; sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Cover leftovers loosely.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine and put in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: danish coconut
directions: Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
Cooking time would depend on the size of the cookie.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in ungreased pan.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozens.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands and roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray. Mix first six (6) ingredients in baking dish.
Stir until smooth. Mix next three (3) ingredients. Sprinkle on top of cake mixture. Do not stir.
Pour coffee on top of cake.
Do not stir.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dressing(turkey or chicken)
directions: Combine all ingredients except the butter, the cornbread and the juice from the chicken; mix together until it's smooth.
Pour it in a long pan.
Melt the butter and pour into the mixture and stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pink cloud frozen salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add honey and continue to beat until blended.
Add strawberries, bananas and marshmallows.
Stir with rubber spatula until coated. Gently fold in whipped cream until well mixed.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cover with foil for continued storage.

title: scrumptious zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini 1/4-inch thick and saute with carrots and onion in 3 tablespoons of butter for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add soup and sour cream; mix well.
Place 3/4 cup of croutons in remaining 1 tablespoon of butter; mix until well coated.
Place mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan; sprinkle the buttered croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Will need 2 Ziploc storage bags.

title: ron's famous onion soup
directions: Mix soup mixture as directed.
Saute onions in a small amount of butter.
Add onions and beef bouillon cubes to soup mixture. Cook about 30 minutes.
To serve, top with Mozzarella or Swiss cheese.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Add baking powder, salt, soda and sugar to flour.
Add oil, buttermilk and yeast mixture; mix like biscuits.
Refrigerate and take out desired amount of dough.
Roll and cut out like biscuits. Let rise 30 minutes before baking.
(You do not have to let them rise but they are lighter if you do.)
Dough will keep in refrigerator for about a week.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter, egg yolks, vanilla and almond.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Sift together the flour and baking soda.
Add to batter alternately with sour cream.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: wild rice stuffed chicken
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions.
Add green onions, raisins and walnuts to cooked rice; mix gently. Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon stuffing into chicken cavity; do not pack. Close chicken cavity with skewers.
Place chicken in roasting pan. Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Brush chicken with butter.
Roast, basting occasionally with pan juices until juices run clear when meat is pierced with a knife, about 55 minutes. Let chicken stand, then carve.
Serve with stuffing.
Serves 6.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Spread frozen loaf with olive oil on cookie sheet, cover with plastic wrap and allow to thaw.
When completely thawed (about 4 hours), stretch to ends of cookie sheet.
Mix paste and sauce and season to taste with Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, basil, minced onion and oregano.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on dough, leaving an inch border all around.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown. Remove and top with your favorite toppings:
mushrooms, green pepper, onions, pepperoni, sausage, etc.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: tender tips
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a small amount of oil. Add broth, sherry, soy sauce, garlic and onion powder.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water and gradually add to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until gravy thickens. Cook 1 minute more. Serve over rice, noodles or toast.

title: butter icing
directions: Combine milk and flour.
Cook until thick, then cool.
Beat sugar and butter together with spoon.
Add cooled mixture and beat 10 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Ready to spread on your favorite cakes, etc.

title: hidden valley ranch party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and green onions.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Sprinkle on red pepper and celery.
Roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends into 1-inch slices. Makes 3 dozen.

title: parmesan mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms (save for another use).
Simmer mushroom caps in a small amount of water for 2 minutes.
Drain, then invert caps on paper towels.
Cool.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds in sugar over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Cool and break apart; store at room temperature.
Place lettuce and romaine in plastic bag; add onion and celery.
Pour Sweet Sour Dressing into bag; add orange segments.
Close bag tightly and shake until well coated.
Add almonds and shake.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, orange juice (that has been mixed with 3 cans water), lemonade (that has been mixed with 3 cans water), sugar and food color.
Stir well.
This mixture may be frozen until needed.
Add ginger ale only when ready to be served.
The red food coloring is my preference; you can leave as is or add your own color.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients over low heat for 10 minutes. Add potatoes.
When potatoes are well cooked, add cheese.
When cheese is melted, add milk.
Do not boil after milk is added.
If you want it thinner, add more milk.
If you want it thicker, use instant mashed potato flakes, not flour.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Soften butter and margarine and combine with sour cream.
Add flour.
Bake in small tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mexican meatballs
directions: Mix. Make into walnut-sized balls and brown after rolling in flour.
Put into sauce and simmer 2 1/2 hours, covered.
Is best made a day ahead.
Great over noodles as a main course or served with toothpicks as an appetizer.

title: "yummy" punch bowl
directions: Soak gelatin in cold milk; dissolve in scalded milk.
Gradually beat sugar into egg yolks.
Pour small amount of hot milk into egg mixture.
Stir into remaining hot mixture.
Combine with cold coffee.
Add vanilla; cool.
Pour into freezer container and freeze.
Let egg whites and custard thaw about 1 1/2 hours.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Break custard into chunks and beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into punch bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush the graham crackers and mix with butter, then press in bottom of pan.
Mix Dream Whip.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and sugar; mix with Dream Whip mixture.
Place on crushed graham crackers.
Top with cherry filling or pineapple.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes in unsalted water until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool; then peel and grate on coarse side of grater. Grate cheese.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, layer 1/2 of the potatoes and onion with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers using remaining potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle cheese over top and pour cream over all as evenly as possible.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, mix sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice. Mix well.
While beating, add oil, slowly, and continue to beat, until thick, then add poppy seed.

title: picadillo
directions: In large heavy skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic, stirring to break up meat, until beef is browned and onion tender. Drain off fat. Stir in tomatoes, raisins, chili powder, cinnamon, salt, cloves and pepper.
Bring to boil.

Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes. Transfer to serving platter. Wipe skillet clean; add almonds and oil. Saute over medium heat until lightly browned. Sprinkle over serving platter. Serve.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and brown sugar. Gradually add white sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Combine baking powder, salt and flour. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in pineapple.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling evenly. Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Dot butter all over top.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: reese cup candy
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter.
Add sugar until firm enough to form balls size of marbles.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Using toothpick, dip balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Yields about 125 balls.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook peeled and dried eggplant in boiling water about 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Beat eggs and mix with milk.
Soak bread in milk-egg mixture.
Add onion, cheese, salt, pepper and eggplant. Mix well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in flour mixture and brown in oil.
Move meat to casserole dish.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in skillet from which meat was removed.
Make gravy by adding flour, water and tomato juice to vegetables.
Pour over meat and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Can serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: never fail icing
directions: Make a thin paste of milk and flour so that you have no lumps. Use all milk.
Cover over very low fire, stirring all the time.
It will be very, very thick.
Cool.
Stir now and then so no scum forms.
When cold, put into small mixing bowl and set aside.
Add rest of ingredients to cooked mixture.
Beat at high speed for 10 minutes.
Will frost 2 eight-inch layers or 24 cupcakes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend together butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Chill.
Form dough into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press crosswise with fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: island cucumbers
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Place in glass jar with a lid and chill in the refrigerator an hour before using.
Cut cucumber into very thin slices and add to the vinegar solution.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges and orange peelings. Pour sugar, nuts, apples and pineapple over it. Prepare jello according to package directions and mix with other ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken on bottom of casserole.
(Butter bottom of casserole.)
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over top.
Split 1 can biscuits.
Put on top. Dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: health salad
directions: Dice all the vegetables to 1/4 inch size. May use processor, but try to get the pieces about 1/4 inch. Marinate in dressing 12-24 hours. Serve.

title: molasses cake
directions: Crumb flour, sugar and Crisco together.
Remove 1 rounded cup of crumbs for top of cake.
Dissolve remaining crumbs in 2 cups boiling water.
Add molasses, baking powder and baking soda; mix.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions. Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: diet chicken breasts
directions: Take boned chicken breasts, flatten slightly; dip into salad dressing and roll in seasoned bread crumbs to which grated cheese was added.
Spray baking sheet with spray cooking oil.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: tomato carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in pot and add onion.
Saute for five minutes.
Add carrots and curry powder.
Cover and cook 20 minutes more.
Remove skin on tomatoes by dipping in boiling water for 30 seconds, then chop coarsely; add tomatoes and chicken broth to saucepan with vegetables.

Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Add 2 tablespoons basil, salt and pepper; simmer 1 minute. Transfer soup to blender or food processor and puree until smooth. Stir in remaining basil.
Serve cold or hot topped with a dollop of sour cream.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1 c. sugar in iron skillet and mix all the other ingredients. Cook slowly until thick. Pour into prepared pie crust.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in flour and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 deep dish pie.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Bone chicken breasts and cut into strips.
Soak in mixture of beaten eggs and garlic powder for 30 minutes or several hours. Heat oil in skillet.
Coat chicken with a mixture of flour and crushed crackers (equal parts of each).
Fry in oil until brown, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook 10 minutes and drain.

title: chocolate lime bisque
directions: Put 1 cup crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; spread evenly. Mix the water, jello, sugar and lemon juice; let cool.
Add grated chocolate.
When beginning to set, whip evaporated milk.
Add gelatin mixture; whip together until thick.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate until set.

title: eagle brand fruit cake
directions: Line 2 loaf pans with waxed paper.
Grease paper.
Mix all ingredients with hands and pack batter into pans well.
Bake around 1 hour at 325°.

title: swiss sandwich puffs
directions: Combine mayonnaise, onions and parsley; spread on rye toast. Top each with 1/4 slice of cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Put in wet ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten.
Bake in uncooked crust at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ladyfinger creme cake
directions: Fold together first 4 ingredients.
Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Pour half of mixture over ladyfingers.
Cut strawberries over mixture; add another layer of fingers.
Spread remaining mixture.
Decorate top with large strawberry.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine meat, onion, seasonings, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 2 cans of water in a 5-quart stew pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add frozen vegetables.
Simmer until tender.
Add canned vegetables.
Simmer. Add 1 package of Ramen noodles with seasoning packet.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Throw all together and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in a 325° oven until firm.
Can be eaten hot or cold.

title: buddy's barbecue sauce
directions: In large pan, mix all preceding.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaves.
Put in pint bottles, taken from boiling water; seal. Store in cool place.
Good on grilled chicken, pork chops, hamburgers or use in baked beans.

title: garlic-butter mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 15 minutes, drain. Meanwhile cook garlic cloves in butter in a skillet over medium-low heat for 3 minutes.
Do no allow garlic to brown. Return potatoes to pot, add the garlic, half and half, salt, and pepper. Mash. Make 8 servings.

title: peanut butter fruit dip(diabetic)
directions: Beat all ingredients until fluffy with electric mixer.
Cover and chill.
Serve with assorted fruit.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.
Per serving:
calories 37, carbohydrates 29, protein 29, fat 39, sodium 10 mg.
Serving size:
1 tablespoon.
Exchange per serving: 1 fat.

title: pear clafoutis
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously butter a 9-inch deep dish glass pie plate.
Beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in medium bowl to blend; whisk in flour.
Add milk, margarine, vanilla and lemon peel and whisk until smooth.
Arrange pears in bottom of the pie plate.
Pour custard over pears.
Bake until Clafoutis is set in center and golden on top, about 55 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Place mixture in a casserole dish and top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt chocolate in 2 cups milk in top of double boiler.
Add salt and sugar; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; beat until foamy.
Add half and half.
Beat; fold in whipping cream.
Cool in refrigerator until ready to freeze (about 30 minutes).

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar (2 tablespoons at a time).
Beat until mixture stands in very stiff peaks.
Fold in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spoon into greased pie pan; make a nest-like shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Place in greased 2-quart casserole in following order: asparagus, eggs, cheese, white sauce and crumbs.
Repeat layers. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
(You can also just add the cheese to the white sauce and layer that way.)

title: mushroom soup(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Chop mushrooms with lemon juice in processor.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add shallots and saute lightly. Add mushrooms, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook, stirring frequently, until liquid is evaporated, about 10 minutes.
Blend in cream, chicken stock, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add dissolved cornstarch and simmer 10 minutes.
Adjust seasonings.
Ladle into heated bowls and sprinkle with parsley.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add pineapple juice to Jell-O and let stand until firm.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in flour and salt and chill for several hours (makes it easy to roll).
You may want to put into 3 bowls (makes it easy to handle).
Roll dough as thin as possible in 10x sugar and cut with a glass or cookie cutter and fold over and seal with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and dust with 10x sugar.

title: grandma thies' peach pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Sprinkle 1/2 in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Arrange fresh peeled peach halves, cut side up, in pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over peaches.

title: instant sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in foil lined pan with enough foil to cover top.
Mix sauces with onion soup mix and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: chinese pickled cucumbers
directions: Wash cucumbers and pare lengthwise in 1/2 to 1-inch strips, leaving every other strip of green skin on.
Cut into halves lengthwise, remove seeds and slice thinly.
Put in bowl and add salt.
Mix well and let stand one hour.
Put in a cloth and squeeze out excess moisture.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and chill.

title: sausage and kale soup
directions: Saute sausage until crisp.
Drain.
Add chicken broth, water, tomato paste, fennel seed and red pepper.
Add kale.
Cook until tender.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix well water, sugar and salt in double boiler; mix well.
Add chocolate.
Cook over rapid boiling water, stirring rapidly.
Cook for 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in stock with onion until soft.
Place in blender and blend quickly.
Make a roux using butter and flour. Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and stock to roux.
To avoid lumps, stir constantly until thickened.
Thin to preferred consistency with cream.
Add seasonings.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in pan. Add eggs.
Stir and cook 3 to 5 minutes until thickened.
Add powdered sugar, nuts and vanilla. Mix well.
(Beat until smooth.) Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Chill in refrigerator.

title: pineapple-noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients except margarine.
Scrape mixture into prepared pan. Dot evenly with margarine.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until set and lightly browned.

title: annie's beef stew
directions: Drain liquid from tomatoes into bowl.
Stir in mustard.
Chop tomatoes.
In 5-quart pot, layer half of potatoes, carrots, mushrooms, onions, garlic and beef.
Sprinkle with tablespoon of flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Top with half the tomatoes and liquid.
Repeat layers.
Add bay leaf.
Cover and bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: pull apart s'mores
directions: Spread peanut butter lightly on graham crackers. Arrange in a single layer in 10 x 15-inch pan. Sprinkle with marshmallows and candies. Broil 6 inches from heat for 2 minutes or until marshmallows begin to melt. Press candies lightly into melted marshmallows. Serve immediately.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown beef with onion and green pepper; drain. Add soup, corn, water, salt and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes. Place in Pam sprayed 13 x 9 baking dish.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust; set aside.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pie filling; mix.
Beat 1 minute or until well blended.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.

Beat sugar, oil and eggs well, then add all dry ingredients and mix very well. Finally, add the carrot, raisin and pineapple mixture and mix. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Check to see if it's done.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: anytime spice cake
directions: Empty spice cake mix in bowl.
Add apple, raisins and nuts. Coat well with mixture.
Add egg whites, milk and cooking oil. Mix well with wooden spoon and pour into Pam-sprayed Bundt pan; bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn on rack to cool.
Use your favorite icing, if desired.
Store in closed container.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups candies; use remaining to decorate tops.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped candies and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Put M&M's on top before baking. Yields 5 dozen.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then cut in with mixer the shortening.
In separate bowl, mash bananas with egg and add to dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and chips.
Stir in by hand.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet with large teaspoon.
Bake at 350°
until firm, not brown.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Steam zucchini until tender (approximately 4 minutes).
Halve lengthwise and hollow out pulp to form boats, reserving pulp. Spray skillet with vegetable spray.
Combine pulp, tomato, basil and thyme and cook over medium heat about 3 minutes.
Add croutons to absorb liquid, then salt and pepper to taste.
Fill boats with mixture; top with cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and milk; let stand a few minutes until most of the milk is absorbed.
Grease twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Heat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into medium size mixing bowl.
Stir to mix well.
Add raisins and nuts; toss to mix.
Add egg and oil to soaked cereal; beat well with a fork.
Pour into flour mixture; stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Drop batter into prepared pans, filling each cup 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake for about 30 minutes, or until browned.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute small amount of garlic powder in 1/2 stick oleo.
Remove from heat and add all remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 cheese cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese with mixer until smooth. Pour in pie shell.
Top with your favorite pie filling.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pear pie
directions: Peel and slice pears; put in large bowl.
Add sugar, cinnamon, flour and whipping cream.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
You can make apple pie the same way.

title: louisiana corn pone
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add a little milk until you can work batter.
Add eggs and beat until mixed well.
Add enough milk to make thin enough to fry like pancakes on a griddle.
Serve warm with butter.

title: beef brisket
directions: Pound meat strongly with fist on both sides.
(I use an old potato masher.)
On each side sprinkle lightly with red pepper, then more liberally with garlic salt and paprika.
Bread wrap brisket with heavy-duty foil (fat side up).
Bake in a 300° oven 4 to 5 hours.
Cool at least 30 minutes before slicing diagonally.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine. Add this and all the rest of the ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Using a microwave dish, melt butter.
Add flour and stir in milk slowly.
Cook on High 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until thick.
Add cheese and garlic powder.

title: apple raisin bread pudding
directions: In greased 2-quart casserole, combine cookies and bread cubes. Combine milk, egg substitute, margarine, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour over cookie mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, bake 20 to 30 minutes more until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings, 158 calories; 175 mg. sodium; 3 grams fat each.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Rinse crabmeat and remove any shell bits.
Mix all ingredients together.
Open English muffins.
Spread mixture onto the 12 halves.
Broil a few minutes and serve.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Sift together
flour,
baking
powder,	baking soda and salt. In mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine on medium speed of electric mixer for	30
seconds.
