Add sugar and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.	Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 5 hours before serving.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large shallow dish.
Set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients, mixing well; pour over vegetables, tossing lightly.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: ice box lemon pie
directions: Melt butter in 9 inch glass pie pan.
Mix graham crackers into butter to make the crust.
Separate egg whites, put egg yolks into 2 cans of milk.
Stir well.
Add lemon juice and stir until thick.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until peeked.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Place on pie and bake until top is brown.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Mix first four ingredients for salad. Mix dressing well, (last four ingredients). When ready to serve put in noodles and dressing, stir well!

title: west indies salad
directions: Wash and dry crabmeat thoroughly.
Add onions, then oil.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Chill before serving.
(Serve with cornbread dressing.)
Serves 6.

title: pizzaburgers(serves 75 to 100.  can be frozen)
directions: Grind together the bologna and cheese. Brown the ground beef and drain. Add to the cheese and bologna mixture. Add salt, oregano, parsley and spaghetti sauce. Mix well. Spread on bun halves and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: *Buy the largest Cool Whip you can find.

title: linda's homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 1/4 c. warm water.
Stir in 1 c. warm water.
add sugar, salt, and shortening.
add 3 1/2 c. flour and stir until smooth.
Add rest of flour to make dough easy to handle.
Place in greased bowl to rise about 2 hours or until double in size.
Divide dough in half and let rest 10 minutes. Grease 2 loaf pans and put dough in pans.
Let rise until double or until pan is full and bake at 400 degrees until brown.
Put melted butter on top before and after baked.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, cream and carrots; fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and butter; spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 11 x 8 x 2 dish. Spoon on vegetable mixture. Top with other half of stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt dorothy's pot roast
directions: Coat meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat in Dutch oven in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Drain grease, if any.
Add 4 cups of water (1/2 way up meat).
Add Italian seasoning, 4 to 5 tablespoons vinegar, bouillon cubes and sugar.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Add water now and then.
Add carrots 1 hour before.
Take out meat.
Add flour and cold water
paste and mix fast.
Add couple drops of Gravy Master.

title: peach butter brickle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour peaches and juice into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Melt margarine and drizzle over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: veggie salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir, turn off, let cool.
Mix next 8 ingredients with cooled dressing mix. Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop and mix together in large bowl first 4 ingredients. Next, mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: whipped cream pie
directions: Scald 1 cup of milk in top of double boiler.
Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add remaining 1/2 cup of milk and make smooth paste. Pour into hot milk and stir until thick.
Beat eggs and add to hot mixture.
Cook for 5 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell. Pile whipped cream on top.

title: finnish spring bread
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, cardamon, orange peel, lemon peel and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter in saucepan over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat two minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour. Beat at high speed two minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: pronto spanish rice
directions: Melt the bacon drippings in a large skillet.
Add the onion, green pepper and rice and cook over medium heat until lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, then set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, stir together flour, sugar and soda.
In a medium saucepan, combine water, margarine and cocoa powder.
Bring just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Add to dry ingredients, beating on low speed of electric mixer just until combined.
Add buttermilk, egg white, egg and vanilla.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute (batter will be thin).
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place Bisquick, salt, pepper, paprika and oregano in a bag.
Coat all pieces of chicken thoroughly.
Put in pan with melted butter, skin side down.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.
It is not necessary to turn the chicken.
If desired, gravy can be made with drippings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli according to pkg. directions.
Cook rice according to directions.
Mix all ingredients and bake in casserole dish in 350° oven for 25-30 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 9 pan.
Dump yellow cake mix on top and spread evenly.	Slice butter and dot on top of cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Bring water and oil to boil.
Add flour, salt, cream of tartar and unsweetened Kool-Aid.
Mix well until blended.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in large bowl. Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt onto waxed paper. Stir into egg mixture until well blended. Stir in nuts. Pour in 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center springs back when pressed.

title: vodka sauce
directions: Saute fresh mushrooms and garlic.
Add tomatoes, vodka, heavy cream, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 40 to 50 minutes, covered.
Serve over penne or large sized rigatoni pasta.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.
Cream shortening and sugar in large mixing bowl until fluffy.
Continue to mix slowly and add eggs, one at a time.
Whip until mixture is light and fluffy.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until well done.
Mix all ingredients.
Put egg yolks in mix.
Cut whites in rings for top.

title: soup italiano(6 servings)
directions: Cut sausage into julienne pieces.
Brown in margarine in large saucepan.
Stir in cole slaw mixture; cook for 1 minute.
Add all but cheese.
Heat slowly to boiling; simmer for 2 minutes.
Ladle into large soup bowls; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: ron's venison jerky
directions: Cut venison into about 1/2-inch strips (longer lengths are best).
Mix all ingredients together with venison strips.
Put into covered container and place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out and place on top oven rack, side by side.
Put foil on bottom rack to catch drips.
Set on lowest oven temperature and bake approximately 4 hours more or less according to dryness of meat (may also use beef).

title: crock pot tacos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Mix all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on	low until hot, about 2 hours. Top with favorite toppings.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients one minute.
Add next 3 ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and allow to cool.

title: "a good jambalaya"
directions: Saute onions in butter in large saucepan for 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and
tomato
paste.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add
garlic, vegetables and seasonings.
Cook for 30 minutes; stir
frequently.	Add ham and shrimp.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in	rice.
Season
to
taste.
Simmer
for	30 minutes; stir frequently.
Yields 8 servings.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Make 3 cups carrots and juice in the blender.
Add a little cream, vanilla, and sugar to taste, a little salt and raisins.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in container and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine and sour cream.
Add other ingredients and pour in greased baking dish.
Bake approximately 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven until golden.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt half stick of
butter in bottom of casserole dish. Brown ground beef and drain.
Chop
cabbage
and put in bottom of dish. Saute bell pepper
and
onion
in
1/4 stick butter. Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle	salt
and pepper.
Spread ground beef and smooth can of tomato
soup	over
that.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes, adding milk and butter sparingly, until creamy.
(Leave somewhat dry.)
Cut luncheon meats, pepperoni and cheese into bite-size pieces.
Add one egg to potatoes and mix.
Add luncheon meats, pepperoni and cheese; mix together.
Put mixture in a baking dish; sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 to 25 minutes (or until cheese melts).
May be served as a main dish meal.

title: apricot fluff
directions: Make jello with 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
When gelatin gels, stir with fork.
Soften cream cheese and add sugar and apricots.
Add jello and whip well.
Fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Chill and garnish with chopped nuts.

title: chicken supreme dijon
directions: Dredge chicken and saute in oil and butter until lightly browned.
Remove chicken to warm plate.
Add 2 1/2 tablespoons of flour to pan and cook 2 to 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add chicken broth and deglaze pan.

title: cold chicken salad
directions: Add enough Miracle Whip salad dressing to coat chicken and fruit.

title: company coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Place frozen dough balls in pan.
Pour melted butter over frozen dough.

title: crab rangoon spread with won ton crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly brush cookie sheet with melted butter.
Cut won ton squares in half.
Arrange rectangles in prepared pan.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on paper towels.
Repeat with remaining won ton squares.
Place cream cheese in glass bowl and soften in the microwave on High power 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in milk and garlic powder.
When well blended, stir in crabmeat and parsley.
Heat 1 to 3 minutes longer until heated. Spread mixture in shallow serving dish.
Top mixture with sweet and sour sauce or have on side.
Serve heated spread with won ton crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 6-inch pan.
Dump pineapple and juice into pan and spread evenly.
Dump in the cherry pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump in the dry cake mix and spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over the cake mix.
Slice butter over that.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 12 to 16 people.
May substitute any kind of pie filling you like.

title: zucchini chips
directions: Sprinkle zucchini lightly with celery salt.
(You may use any seasoning you like.)
Dehydrate 8 to 12 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and garlic in salad oil.
Add 2 large cans Italian tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours. Meanwhile, boil lasagna.
Cool noodles.
Place layers of lasagna.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter; add garlic.
Cover first 15 minutes to wilt onions.
Uncover and add sugar (sugar helps browning).
Cook until a nice brown color; during this period keep a careful watch and stir as needed.
Add flour and stir a few minutes.
Add stock and simmer.
Add wine last 15 minutes.
Serve by placing a dry or slightly toasted slice of French bread in bottom of bowl.
Add soup and top with cheese.
Place bowls on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 350° until melted.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Beat egg, cheese, milk and pepper until blended.
Cook on low heat bacon, garlic and oil until bacon is crisp.
Remove and crumble bacon then return it to the pan.
Pour bacon mixture over hot spaghetti, toss well.
Add egg mixture and toss well.
Serve with additional Romano cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart round greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered) or microwave on High 12 minutes.
May be prepared ready to cook the day before and refrigerated outright.
May also be frozen before cooked (does not freeze well after cooking).
Shred cheese.

title: chocolate banana pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Whip.
Add melted chocolate chips. Pour into pie crusts.
Bake 20-25 minutes until crust is done.
Slice bananas and lay over chocolate.
Mix pudding with 1/2 cups milk. Let set. Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour over banana slices.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips if desired.

title: blue-vue blueberry delight
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix blueberries, pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar in dish and spread evenly along bottom.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit and smooth out the edges of dish.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over cake mix and then follow with 1/4 cup sugar, being careful not to sprinkle too much sugar in one spot.
Drizzle melted butter over mix and bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli
directions: Select stalks of broccoli with dark green, lightly closed buds.
Cut off tough part of stalk and coarse leaves.
Steam or cook, uncovered, in boiling salted water for 15 to 30 minutes. Serve with melted butter or thin white cheese sauce.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat a large shallow baking pan with cooking spray.
Remove the mushroom stems and chop coarsely. Arrange the mushroom caps on pan, cavities facing up.
Brush insides and edges with 2 tablespoons of the oil.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: To prepare grapevine leaves, rinse leaves thoroughly in cold running water to remove brine.
Bring 1 quart of water to a boil; add leaves and parboil 3 minutes.
Drain.
Select 4 or 5 heavy leaves and line bottom of a medium size Dutch oven; set aside.

title: king's fruit salad(kids' recipe)
directions: Open cans of grapefruit and pineapple; drain juice.
Save juice for your own fruit drink.
Put fruit in a small mixing bowl. Peel bananas and cut them into penny slices.
Add them to bowl. Pour in the orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir gently.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator to chill for 1 hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Boil water.
Pour in Jell-O and mix well.
Add marshmallows and stir until partially melted.
Add milk, mayonnaise, pineapple, cherries, cottage cheese and nuts and stir thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator until congealed firmly.

title: blueberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar and grated orange rind.
Cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Fold in blueberries. Combine sour cream and milk; blend into blueberry mixture and mix lightly until dough masses together.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix, but do not beat, ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover the dough thickly with fresh peeled apple slices.
Sprinkle the top with white sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
Will serve 15.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: In a large saucepot, brown beef and vegetables in oil.
Stir in spices and seed.
Add water and tomatoes.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Blend flour and water together until smooth.
Blend into soup and boil 1 minute.
Makes about 8 1/2 cups of delicious soup.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter; beat.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Roll out, cut and fry.

title: fruit and vegetable salad
directions: Cut up the fruit and vegetables, then put dressing on the ingredients and stir.
Taste.
Eat.
Yum yum.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven with enough water to cover. Cover tightly with lid; simmer for 40 minutes, until meat falls from bone.
Remove chicken; let cool.
Discard skin and bone; shred meat.
In a large bowl, mix soup concentrates and tomatoes. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer a third of the tortilla chips, a third of the cooled chicken, a third of the grated cheese and a third of the soup mixture.
Repeat layers, reserving a little cheese and crushed chips for the top.
Bake for 1 hour, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with olives, tomato and lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: hot brats
directions: Cut knockwurst into 1-inch pieces and brown in skillet.
Add beer and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and blend in vinegar, mustard and horseradish.
Add to sausage. Cook and stir until thick.
Place in a fondue pot and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter for 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Combine all other ingredients, except chips.
Mix well.
Place chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, milk, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add butter. Gradually add warm water and beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 45 minutes.
Punch down and allow to rise again 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half and cut each into 10 pieces.
Form into rolls and place on greased sheet.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: deviled mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft (5 minutes).
Add bread crumbs, seasonings and soy sauce.
Fill mushroom caps.
Place in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in Bundt cake pan (spray pan with Pam).	Cook for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Take out immediately and put in airtight container.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all the water out.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add sour cream, soup mix, onion, mayonnaise and spinach; stir well.
Then add crab meat and water chestnuts. Chill in refrigerator.
Good served with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Best when made day before.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off most of fat.
Add to rest of ingredients in large pot and bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes on low.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add mashed bananas, orange juice, pineapple and lemon juice and 4 juice cans of water.
Freeze. Thaw 30 minutes before using.
Pour ginger ale over thawed frozen mixture.
Serves 20.

title: holiday franks
directions: Combine ketchup, wine and sugar in saucepan.
Add franks after each has been cut into 4 or 8 pieces.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Can be prepared the day before and reheated.
Add 1/4 cup of wine, if reheated.
Serve in chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: citrus sherbet
directions: Mix sugar and milk. Add fruit juice. Partially freeze, then fold in the whipped cream. Finish freezing. Makes a nice, smooth, and not too rich dessert.

title: corn fritters
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together creamed corn, baking power, corn meal, flour and garlic salt.
In another bowl, beat together eggs and then mix all together.
Spoon it out in a frying pan of oil or shortening.

title: czech doughnuts
directions: In
a
large
bowl dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk (1/2 cup). Add
cup
of
sugar,
1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 cups flour. Let
stand in warm place 1/2 hour.
Beat egg yolks and whole
egg lightly.
Add
cup sugar and vanilla and beat lightly.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add melted margarine and rest of
the
flour. Do
not make dough too stiff.
A softer dough makes doughnuts light and fluffy.
Work the dough until smooth and
glossy.
Cover and let stand in a warm place until double in bulk.

title: mini cherry cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with liners.
Place one wafer in each liner. Soften cream cheese in a bowl and add sugar gradually.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Spoon into liners evenly about 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° until set, about 10-15 minutes.
Remove from pan, but do not remove liners.
Cool on wire racks.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of pie filling.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl, break eggs over apples.
Stir with fork.
Add sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, oil and nuts.
Add flour gradually.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 50 minutes or more.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in 2-inch cubes.
Parboil eggplant and onion; drain off excess water.
Mix together all other ingredients; place in casserole dish.
Place sliced Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
My family loves this dish!

title: bubbling jade punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and pineapple juice.
Mix lemonade concentrate with cold water.
Mix with jello mixture; blend well.
DO NOT refrigerate.
Just before serving pour into punch bowl and slowly add ginger ale.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Serve with apples.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Blend into mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.

title: meatless vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot on medium heat.
Add carrots, cabbage, onion, celery and rosemary.
Saute until tender and starting to brown (about 10 minutes).
Add broth and tomatoes with juice and simmer about 45 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Stir in cheese and serve.
Additional grated cheese can be put on top when served.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown meat slowly. Spoon off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour. Stir now and then.

title: "no stick" cake pan liner
directions: Blend until smooth with electric mixer.
Store in a tightly closed glass or plastic container in the refrigerator.
Use to line pans for any recipe that calls for "grease and flour." Spread on pans with a paper towel.
Stays good indefinitely if stored in a tightly closed container in the refrigerator.

title: candied pecans
directions: Melt margarine at 275° in a jelly roll pan.

title: pizza dough
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, salt and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine yeast to milk mixture.
Make stiff dough. Knead 5 to 10 minutes. Place dough in greased bowl. Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Roll out and put on pizza pan. Add sauce and add favorite topping.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.
Line pan (13 x 9-inch) with graham crackers.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture, then sliced bananas (optional).
Place layer of graham crackers, then 1/2 pudding mixture and another layer of graham crackers. Microwave can of chocolate frosting.
Pour over top.
Chill.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Set in refrigerator over night.
Next day bring to a boil (a full rolling boil).
Add a few fresh strawberries (mashed).
Remove from fire and add 1 small package strawberry jello.
Stir until it is well dissolved.
Pour in jars and refrigerate.

title: zucchini torta (frittata)(mariapolis recipe)
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise in 4, then cut in cubes.
Cut onions in cubes.
Saute onion and zucchini in olive oil.

Add crushed garlic or garlic powder, crushed red pepper and pinch of salt. When vegetables are almost cooked (onions are transparent), add bread crumbs and the eggs (beaten with 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese).
Add the tomatoes.

title: brad's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Add beaten eggs and beat. Stir in peanut butter. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Press with back of fork to make crisscross design. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: better than sex chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still hot, poke good sized holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over top of cake.
Next, spread butterscotch caramel ice cream topping on cake.
After cake is cool, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with broken up Heath bar or toffee bits. Delicious and rich!

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl, place in casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine zwieback crumbs and sugar.
Butter sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Shake some of the crumbs around pan to coat sides.
Add melted butter to rest of crumbs and blend well.
Press over bottom of pan.
Meanwhile, melt chocolate with coffee over hot (not boiling) water.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Scrape down sides of bowl and beat again.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Beat in melted chocolate until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 55 minutes.
Turn off heat; set oven door ajar and let cool 2 to 3 hours.
Spread with whipped cream and sprinkle with shaved chocolate.
Serve at room temperature.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease large muffin tins and pour them about 3/4 full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 16 to 18 muffins.

title: coconut-sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) layers.
When cool, split each layer, making 4.

title: persimmon cookies(store with paper towels between layers)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, spices, salt, baking powder, lemon juice, vanilla and fruit pulp.
Beat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix flour and lard with pastry blender.
Add sugar, salt, egg and water.
Mix well.
Yields 5 shells.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spread chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put onion, 1/2 package of Doritos and cheese over chicken.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and small amount of cayenne; pour over.
Put other 1/2 package of crushed Doritos on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy mustard sauce by laura
directions: Melt butter or oleo in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly or until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Remove about 1/4 of the hot mixture and add to the beaten egg yolk.
Add to the remaining hot mixture along with the salt, pepper and mustard. Stir constantly and slowly add the lemon juice.
Serve over hot cooked vegetables.
Yield: One cup.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put sugar, Crisco and salt into bowl.
Add warm mashed potatoes and mix.
Add egg to warm milk.
Mix together.
Add yeast 1 pint flour.
Gradually add to mixture.
Beat well as you mix. Add enough flour to knead.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Mash down and place in refrigerator until needed.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese and cream with butter.
Add flour, salt and sugar; chill.
Make into tiny biscuits; put 1/2 pecan on top of each (optional).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking pan.
Cover with vinegar-water mixture.
Spread ketchup over the top, then add chopped celery. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Mix the two ingredients together and heat; add cooked cocktail meatballs.

title: hot pears
directions: Mix preserves and vermouth together and pour over fruit. Top with crushed macaroons or lemon cookies. Heat in 350° oven until it bubbles. Serves 8 to 10.

title: indian stew
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all vegetables and seasonings. Simmer 3 hours.

title: quick bean dip
directions: Slice Velveeta into 1-inch pieces and mix with other ingredients in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish with lid. Microwave three minutes and mix thoroughly.
Microwave three more minutes and mix thoroughly.
Serve with dip-size tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash avocados in bowl with lemon juice and jalapeno peppers. Combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix in another bowl.
Layer on shallow serving platter:
Bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives, in that order. Serve with round tortilla chips.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Cover beans with water and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer until beans are tender.
Drain; reserve 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add chili sauce, vinegar, mustard, salt, horseradish, curry powder, red pepper and reserved cooking liquid.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add beans; simmer 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach on paper towels.
Combine spinach, water chestnuts and remaining ingredients; cover and chill.
Garnish, if desired, with celery leaves and pimento strips, and serve with assorted fresh vegetables.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Marinate all over night in refrigerator. Stir once or twice.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and milk.
Mix in beef, onion, pepper and sour cream.
Spoon into ovenproof serving dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serve as a dip for raw vegetables or with crackers.

title: orange cranberry muffins
directions: Cut orange in pieces (rind and all) remove any seeds.
Drop pieces into blender with orange juice and blend until peel is finely chopped.
Drop in cranberries, egg and butter.
Blend.

title: oatmeal crunch cookies
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Stir in milk and dry mixture. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Makes 42 cookies.

title: chicken livers in italian sauce
directions: Saute chicken livers in oil in a large skillet 5 or 8 minutes or until brown.
Remove livers from skillet; chop and set aside. Add onion and celery to skillet.
Saute until tender.
Return livers to skillet and add next 12 ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Serve liver mixture over noodles and sprinkle with cheese.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: short cut lasagne
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef.
Add to the spaghetti sauce and water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Layer sauce, noodles (overlap) and cheese mixture. Top with cheese.
Cook at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, soda, nutmeg and pumpkin pie spice together.
Add beaten eggs, pumpkin, water and oil. Combine both mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: "ms. faye's" mexican magic
directions: Brown meat with onion. Add soup, beans, taco seasoning, Ro-Tel and water. Simmer at least 15 minutes. Line pan or dish with broken chips. Add layer of meat mixture and layer of cheese; keep layering chips and meat, ending with cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until bubbles. Can add last layer of cheese after it's done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat until browned.
Drain. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with pizza sauce and cheese. Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over casserole, covering evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Then slowly pour through a funnel into fry pan containing deep fat or oil.
Eat, topped with powdered sugar.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour and sugar with 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix in egg yolks.
Add this slowly to boiling water.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Cook and pour into baked crust.
Beat egg white and add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: peanut butter-chocolate squares candy
directions: Cream together margarine and powdered sugar.
Blend in graham crackers, peanut butter and Karo syrup (hands work best here). Press evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Pour over the peanut butter mixture.
When chocolate has set, cut into squares.
Refrigerate until hard (do not refrigerate before cutting because chocolate will crack).

title: pineapple-angel dessert
directions: Lightly drain the pineapple.
In medium saucepan, cook pudding according to directions, then add pineapple and juice. Cook a little longer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Slice cake and put a single layer in a 9 x 9-inch pan, cutting to fit.
Top with half of the pudding/pineapple mixture. Add another layer of cake and the rest of the pudding.
Refrigerate until cool, then frost with Cool Whip. Decorate each piece with a maraschino cherry. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken pepperoni
directions: Cook chicken breasts in oil until done; drain and set aside. Combine picante sauce, Italian seasonings, green pepper and pepperoni.
Heat to boil and add cubed chicken; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve on top of rice or mix with noodles and serve. Garnish with cheese.

title: tassies
directions: To make the filling, mix ingredients together. Drop by tablespoon into each crust. Bake 25 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan and lay wax paper across width and sides.
Pour batter into pan; bake according to box directions.
While baking, mix flour and water; boil until it thickens.
Cool completely.
Mix flour mixture with remaining ingredients and beat until fluffy. When cake is done, lift out by paper and flip onto second wax sheet.
Cool.
Cut into horizontally with dental floss.
Put fluffy mix between layers.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix tapioca and V-8 juice together.
Place all ingredients in large Dutch oven or similar baking dish.
Bake 5 hours at 350°.

title: dishwasher cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix all other ingredients and blend together well.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 dozen.

title: chicken in white cream sauce
directions: Put chicken into baking dish.
Combine flour with 1/2 cup sour cream; mix until smooth.
Add soup, wine and sour cream; mix until smooth.
Add salt, paprika and pimentos; mix.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle on almonds.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Cook oatmeal in boiling water, then add shortening, brown sugar and salt.
In a separate cup, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Put oatmeal mixture in large bowl, then add yeast water.
Add 3 to 4 cups of flour and mix until contents of bowl can be removed to floured countertop.
Knead in more flour until dough consistency is okay.
The dough will feel tacky and can be pinched into a peak, but won't stick to counter.
If too much flour is added, sprinkle small amounts of water on the dough.
Knead for at least 10 minutes.
Put dough in large bowl and cover, allowing it to rise for 1 hour.
Remove dough and push it down.
Do not knead the dough.
Cut the dough in half and put the halves into two greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake loaves for 50 minutes on middle shelf. Remove loaves to cooling rack and cover.
Don't slice until cooled to lukewarm.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and dry ingredients with mixture.
Add rest by spoon.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Zap it with your favorite topping.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and sour milk.
Add cocoa, cloves, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add flour and mix well.
Add zucchini.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry beets
directions: Put beets and cranberry sauce into saucepan and heat until blended.
Stir in orange rind, then cornstarch which has been dissolved in cold water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Fine with all pork dishes.
Leftovers reheat well.
Yields 4 servings.
Double recipe to serve 6 to 8.

title: baked potatoes and cheddar
directions: Spread frozen hash browns in a baking dish.
Mix soup with equal canned milk.
Melt cheese in soup.
Pour mixture over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil whole heads of cabbage to soften top leaves.
Pull off top leaves; set aside.

title: dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing bowl the next 8 ingredients.
Add yeast mixture and flour.
Stir well to combine.
Let rise in greased bowl to double in size.
Punch down. Put into two 7 x 3-inch or one 9 x 5-inch well-greased bread pans.
Let rise again about 45 to 50 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and brush with melted butter.

title: green bean appetizer
directions: Drain green beans.
Wrap 6 to 8 whole green beans in 1/2 slice bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place in glass dish.

title: cumin chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Combine 1 teaspoon of the cumin, oregano and garlic salt; mix well.
Rub into chicken. Lightly brown chicken in oil in large skillet; drain off fat. Combine remaining cumin, picante sauce, water and instant bouillon, mixing well; pour over chicken.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken to serving platter; keep warm.
Cook and stir sauce mixture in skillet over medium-high heat until liquid is reduced and sauce is slightly thickened.
Skim fat from sauce; drizzle sauce over chicken.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: brown rice side dish
directions: Cook rice according to instructions on the box; set aside. Saute finely chopped onion in butter.
Scramble eggs and add to onion.
Stir in rice.
Add soy sauce.
Mix well.
Heat side dish on low in large frypan until main dish is ready.

title: venison casserole
directions: Cut up onion.
Microwave until soft.
In silverstone pan brown meat.
Add onion and water and heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pam large casserole dish and pour mixture into it.
Pare and thinly slice potatoes.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.
Serves about 6.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer chicken, broccoli and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place topping on and cook 15 minutes longer, until heated through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: popcorn scramble
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large roasting pan.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to boil, then lower heat.
Stir constantly.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour mixture over first 4 ingredients.
Stir until mixture is well coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Be sure to stir every 5 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix in blender; toss with salad greens.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and chill before serving.
Stir and drain.

title: cheese and chicken quiche
directions: Combine the ingredients and pour into the unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until set.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown onions in oleo and add all other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add 2 pounds cooked and salted pork or beef and simmer in sauce.
Serve on warm buns.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all together in the freezer container.
Recipe makes 1 gallon.
Freeze ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add salad oil, sugar, vanilla and shredded zucchini.
Mix lightly.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder and nuts and mix lightly.
Butter 2 regular size loaf pans or 6 mini loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken
broth until tender.
Mix sour cream, soups, mushrooms, juice
and cheese.
Layer broccoli in a
x 13-inch glass
dish.
Top
with
chicken.
Spoon
soup mixture over and spread
evenly.
Mix crumbs and margarine and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° until crumbs brown and casserole is bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: onion-cheese pie
directions: Mix crumbs and 3/8 cup margarine. Press into greased pie pan to make crust.
Chop onions and saute in 2 tablespoons margarine until golden.
Spread on crust.

title: apples and dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut apples and sprinkle with Fruit-Fresh, then dip into mixture.

title: marshmallow pudding with angel food cake
directions: Take 1 tablespoon Knox gelatine.
Add 1/2 cup water and set on stove and stir constantly over low heat until dissolved.
Set off and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Beat egg whites stiff and add salt. Pour gelatine slowly over egg whites, add sugar and stir.
Add vanilla and pour into loaf pan to mold.
Cool in refrigerator. Unmold and serve a slice over slice of angel food cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Put flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a bag.
Put 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in bag and shake until coated.
Put oil in pan or baking dish, then place chicken in dish and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Turn over and bake 30 minutes longer or until it is done. (You can freeze this.)

title: easy guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with a fork.
Add sour cream and taco seasoning; mix well.

title: the king's copper penny carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Arrange layers of carrots, bell pepper and onion in container.
Make a marinade of the other ingredients and heat well until blended.
Pour over carrots.
Keep refrigerated. Will keep for weeks and liquid may also be used again.
Recipe may be doubled.
Serves 12.

title: sweet cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and onion.
Add vinegar, light Karo syrup, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise, one spoon at a time, until slightly juicy.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: berried delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and chill.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk and fold in whipped cream.
Spread mixture over chilled crust and arrange 2 pints of berries on top.
Mix Blair pie mix according to directions.
Cool 15 minutes then pour onto 1 3/4 cups whipped cream and garnish with berries.
Pineapple can be used in place of berries.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together dressing, cream cheese and ham. Roll into ball. Chill. Roll ball in nuts until covered. Serve with crackers.

title: coconut crunch delight
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; press lightly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 10 minutes to form coarse crumbs. Cool. Divide crumb mixture in half; press half into the same baking pan. In a mixing bowl, beat pudding mixes and milk. Fold in whipped topping; spoon over the crust. Top with remaining crumb mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with strawberries, if desired. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: fudge cocoa brownies
directions: Grease pan.
Melt butter and baking cocoa. Stir well. Add sugar and mix. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Stir in vanilla, flour and salt. Fold in nuts.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: deep dish apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray an 8-inch baking dish.
Place half of the apples in dish; top with corn syrup.
Add remaining apples, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, sugar, salt, margarine, flour and oatmeal.
Mix and press firmly over apples.
Bake 50 minutes.
To serve, top with ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Serves 10.
Can be refrigerated and baked later.

title: ham rolls
directions: Using a mixer, mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Fold in chives.
Spread a slice of ham with cream cheese mix; add a slice of cheese, then spread more cheese mixture.
Roll longways into a jelly roll.
Chill for several hours.
Then cut into 1-inch pinwheels.
Great served with chilled olives.

title: breakfast pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until tender.
Drain and return to the pan.
Beat egg and pour over hot pasta along with butter and cheese.
Place over low heat and stir until egg is set on the pasta and cheese is melted.

title: hot water gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together shortening and brown sugar, add egg and beat until light. Blend or sift together flour, baking soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon. Combine molasses and hot water. Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture, alternating with the molasses and hot water. Blend until well combined. Pour batter into a greased 8-inch square pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with spiced whip cream or Foamy Applesauce.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix lightly together.
Just before serving, add small amount of mayonnaise.

title: hamburger and noodles casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Layer mixture and cheese in oblong (6 x 9-inch) casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: little smokies
directions: Heat jelly, catsup and lemon juice.
Add smoked sausage or Little Smokies or meat balls.
Cook until heated through.

title: sauerkraut reuben casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sauerkraut in pan.
Top with corned beef, then cheese.
Pour dressing on top of cheese.
Add sliced tomatoes.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine and saute rye crackers for 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread on top of dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain artichokes, coarsely chopped and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a small casserole dish uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers, cocktail bread, or fresh vegetables.

title: easy cherry filled cookies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar until light and fluffy. Mix 2 eggs together. Add 2 more eggs and vanilla, then slowly add flour. Grease and flour cookie sheet. Spread dough on, cut into 24 squares. Put 1 tsp. of pie filling in center of each square. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: great northern bean stew
directions: In a large saucepan or 4-quart Dutch oven.
Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: sandy's low-fat lasagne
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and water to desired thickness.
Simmer on medium-low, stirring 45 minutes. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with a little sauce, layer noodles and cheese (makes 5 layers).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let set 20 minutes; cut and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients and pour into round dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Mix in qt. jar in order named and shake vigorously.
Be sure to always add oil last. It is very good on sliced tomatoes.

title: new potatoes
directions: Boil small new potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain almost dry.
Leave 3 or 4 teaspoons water in kettle.
Sprinkle in meal and swish around to coat all potatoes.
Heat shortening and fry potatoes until brown, about 10 minutes, turning to brown all sides.

title: hearty tomato-beef soup
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and celery in melted butter in large saucepan until meat is well browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop or grind peppers and onions.
Combine with other ingredients and boil 20 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: southern (holland) pink pear delight
directions: Peel the pears, leaving the stem attached.
Into each pear, stick 1 clove.
Place in deep pot.
Add sugar, wine, water and food coloring to give desired color.
Simmer very gently until pears are clear and syrup is thick, basting now and then.
Chill.
Serve cold as salad or dessert.

title: flu stew
directions: Put stew beef in casserole pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over beef.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, covered.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain the fruit, and mix together.
Stir 1 can apricot pie filling over the mixture.

title: frozen strawberry cake
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Add 3/4 cup strawberries and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slow until changes color or about 20 minutes. Cool and put into freezer bags and freeze and date day.
If you don't want creamed corn don't add the cream, just add the butter, salt and sugar.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt and let stand 3 hours. Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Boil until transparent. Seal in jars.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse.
Chop everything. Then add to spaghetti.
Chill.
Before serving, add croutons.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: perpetual bran muffins
directions: Pour hot water over cereal.
Add buttermilk and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to cereal.
Add shortening.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Stir just until mixed.
Do not overmix.
Put in jars and store in refrigerator.
Keeps 5 to 6 weeks.
Do not stir when taking out.
To bake, fill muffin pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cold reuben spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and cocktail sauce in a medium bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Serve with bread or rye crackers. Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.
Can use canned beef from Super Market Deli.

title: seven-up salad and topping
directions: Drain pineapple juice and save for topping.
Add hot water to Jell-O, stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add Seven-Up, pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Chill overnight.

title: lucille's german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins, peel and slice.
Cut-up bacon fine and fry until crisp.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Cook sauce ingredients until thick.
Add bacon and onions with grease to sauce and pour over sliced potatoes; mix.
If you want to make it early, it warms well in microwave.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together and add enough milk and water (about 1 1/2 cups) to make as soft a dough as can be rolled out.
Roll out 1 inch thick.
Cut into biscuits and place close together in buttered tin.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: marinated hot dogs
directions: Mix and simmer 2 hours.

title: good beans
directions: Fry bacon, beef and onion until lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: sausage and cabbage
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add sliced sausage, coarsely shredded cabbage, diced onion and crushed garlic.
Cook until almost tender (8 minutes).
Stir frequently.
Add mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir and heat 4 minutes.
Serve.

title: kyle's gingersnaps
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add molasses. Gradually add flour while mixing, then add baking soda and spices. Roll dough into balls with white granulated sugar, rolled on as a covering.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Time in oven determines crispness.

title: onion baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking pan. Salt and pepper. Place pats of butter or margarine on chicken.
Pour soup over chicken and add mushrooms. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas under running cold water to separate.
Heat peas, chicken soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup milk, salt and pepper just to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; keep warm while preparing biscuits.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add cocoa then add sugar. Stir over medium heat until shiny.
Then add milk.
Stir until boiling.
Take off of heat - add vanilla.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
After noodles are cooked, place in a casserole dish.
Add tuna and soup.
Add 1/2 can of water to soup; mix well.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add one egg at a time. Add vanilla and milk.
Pour into crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions in melted shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Pour meat mixture into a greased 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with corn bread batter, spreading carefully with a wet knife.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry figs
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Put in jars and heat seal.

title: turkey-vegetable soup
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine undrained tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: reuben sausage
directions: Pare and cube potatoes. Combine sauerkraut, potatoes (2 cups), sausage, dressing and parsley. Spoon into greased 10 x 6 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese and green pepper strips over the top. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, salt and water for 20 minutes, turning once.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes, stirring every minute. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: rice and barley casserole
directions: Saute barley and rice in 2 tablespoons butter.
Put into casserole dish.
Saute onion and mushrooms separately.
Add to casserole with chicken broth and season with salt and pepper. Bake until broth is absorbed 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 pounds fudge
directions: Cook together milk, sugar, margarine and vanilla for 9 minutes.
(Begin timing when mixture starts to boil.) Remove from heat and add chips and marshmallow cream.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Place shredded cabbage in hot bacon oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add sugar and cook 10 more minutes on medium high.

title: stuff french toast
directions: Cut 1 pound loaf of day old white sandwich bread into cubes. Spread half of bread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut cream cheese into small cubes.
Sprinkle half over bread in pan. Repeat, layering with remaining bread and cheese.
Whisk eggs, milk and syrup in large bowl.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes. Serve warm with additional syrup.
Serves 10.

title: delicious salad
directions: Toss veggies with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Add dressing to vegetable mixture. Store in refrigerator.

title: never fail rolls (angel biscuit)
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg.
Add liquids and flour alternately.
Place large bowl, cover, and put in refrigerator. When ready to cook, roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise 15 minutes before cooking. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix dill weed, garlic powder, lemon pepper and dressing with oil.
Pour onto crackers and mix.
Put in Ziploc bags or airtight container.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken wing sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add hot sauce (3/4 bottle) and Worcestershire sauce to color.
Sprinkle in red peppers and garlic salt.
Add dash of lemon juice.
Simmer.

title: cheezy carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots. Cook until tender and drain. Saute onion in oleo. Add cheese. Heat until melted, stirring constantly. Stir in carrots. Spoon in 2-quart baking dish. Top with potato chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly. Makes 12 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 batter in 9 x 13 cake pan and bake for 20 minutes at temperature listed on box.
Remove cake from oven.
Put 1/2 the caramel spread in a saucepan with a small amount of butter to get warmed for easier spreading.	Once warmed, pour the caramel over the cake and spread it.
Sprinkle 1 c. of pecans and 4 oz. of chocolate chips over that.
Pour the remaining batter on top of the cake and bake for approximately 20-30 minutes.
When bringing out of the oven, put rest of chocolate chips over top of cake along with rest of the caramel spread so they melt a little.
When all done, spread another cup or 2 of pecans over top.
Enjoy!

title: crunchy drop cookies
directions: Hand beat shortening, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pineapple slices
directions: Beat all together.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cherry-cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix
first
4 ingredients together thoroughly.	Place 1 vanilla
wafer
in the bottom of each cupcake liner.
Fill 3/4 full
of
cream
cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Place
cherry pie filling on top of each baked cupcake.
Makes 22 to 23 cupcakes.
Blueberry or any pie filling makes a good topping.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, buttermilk and soda together.
Melt butter and pour into square baking dish.
Add flour mixture and stir in fruit.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: braised wild duck
directions: Rub duck pieces well with salt and pepper, and brown well in the butter in a deep heavy pot on top of the stove.
Reduce heat. Add pieces of apples and onion and the wine.
Cover tightly and cook over very low heat until nearly tender (about one hour).

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together and beat for 4 minutes.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture until all used.
Chill and enjoy!!!

title: pear-pineapple crisp
directions: Mix and spread over any type of thickened fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken italia
directions: Wash and debone chicken breast.
Pat dry.
Coat with Italian bread crumbs, after seasoning with salt and pepper.
Place in a pan lined with foil.
Spray with Pam cooking spray to keep breasts from sticking.
Melt the Promise margarine and drizzle over the chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with rosemary.
Cover with foil and place in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, onion and bell pepper together; drain off grease.
Wash and cut up cabbage; put in with sausage.
Pour tomatoes on top of cabbage.
Cover; cook on low for about an hour. It is better warmed up the next day.

title: microwave remarkable fudge
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, combine sugar and milk.
Add butter or margarine.
Cook, uncovered, on High 5 minutes, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil, stirring twice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 9 x 12-inch dish. Combine the broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onions and egg. Blend well.
Pour into a prepared dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot top with butter.
Bake about 35 minutes.

title: children's finger paint
directions: Mix cornstarch with water.
Bring to boil until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Pour into containers.

title: italiano marinara
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook onions until tender.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, garlic, basil, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
Cook for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: doughnuts
directions: Rise once and roll out.
Let rise until double in size, then fry.
Glaze or sugar while doughnuts are warm.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk. Pour over cheese.
Do not cover pan during baking.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: corn chowder(quick and easy)
directions: Combine soup, water and corn.
Stir well and cook on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: deluxe macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together in a baking dish; cover.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients, except broccoli.
Cut broccoli into small pieces; toss all ingredients and cover.
Chill overnight.

title: snack oyster crackers
directions: Thoroughly mix oil, dry dressing mix and dill weed.
Add oyster crackers and stir to coat with oil mixture.

title: flan
directions: Boil milk, cinnamon and lemon peel; let cool.
Beat rapidly the egg yolks, egg whites, sugar and vanilla extract; add this to the milk mixture.
Pour desired amount of caramel into baking dish, then drain entire mixture onto dish.
Place a baking pan full of water in oven, then place other pan over and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally. Add your wieners and simmer 30 to 40 minutes longer, then put into crock-pot.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Do not beat, stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Measure into mixing bowl 1/2 cup warm water.
Add the yeast. Stir in the milk, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine and flour. Beat until smooth (100 strokes). Cover and let rise until light (about 1 hour).
Beat down and pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Let rise within 1-inch of top of pan. Bake until golden brown and crusty. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, apple and carrots; mix these together with mayonnaise.
Add sugar and salt to taste.

title: ambrosia salad mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 10 minutes; stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours at least.

title: best fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a large, heavy saucepan and slowly bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.
Beat just until melted. Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in large ungreased pan and cool.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine; add the next 9 ingredients and pour mixture over the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in a 200° oven for 2 hours, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes a very large amount.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and cold water.
When mixture begins to jell, spoon over Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Mix corn meal, 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and pepper in gallon ziploc bag.
Dip steak into buttermilk or eggs.
Drop into bag and shake.
Remove steak from bag and brown, then cook until done. Mix milk, 1/4 cup flour and gravy mix in skillet.
Bring to boil. Simmer and stir in mushrooms.
Pour over steak.
Bake or microwave until steak is heated back to temperature for serving.

title: gail's squash
directions: Cut up enough vegetables to make a potful.
Cook and drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and put in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Mix well.
Roll thin.
Place dough on baking sheets and bake 5 minutes at 275°, turning once. Cut immediately.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion with margarine.
Add ground beef and brown.
Salt and pepper to taste; add sugar and water, then tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan, layer sauce with noodles and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Dice the broccoli stems and place them in a saucepot with the chicken stock.
Simmer until tender.
In a 3-quart saucepot, saute the diced carrots, celery and onions in the chicken fat with salt and pepper and cook until onion begins to change color.
Reduce heat and add flour to absorb fat.
Stir constantly and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Puree the tender broccoli stems and stock.
Add this to carrot mixture; mix well.
Bring to boil and simmer.
Add 1 1/2 cups of broccoli tops to soup.
Add milk.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size casserole.
Layer bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: one pot supper
directions: Cook macaroni until done and drain. Place back into pan. Brown ground beef and drain off fat. Add beef to macaroni. Add tomatoes, soup, cheese, salt, pepper and just enough milk to where you can see it at the edge of the mixture in pan. Heat on low to medium heat just long enough to melt cheese and all ingredients to blend.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add
taco
mix
and 1 1/2 cups water. Simmer 20
minutes.
Layer tortilla chips, hamburger mixture, taco sauce,
hot
peppers,
sour cream, black olives, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese (optional).

title: cheese nut grapes
directions: Prepare day ahead.
Mix cream cheese and Roquefort or Blue cheese together.
Shape around grapes.
Roll in toasted, chopped almonds or pecans and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate.
Next day, cut grapes in half.
These are so pretty arranged on a serving dish and, for variety, leave some of the grapes whole.

title: apple muffins
directions: Bake in greased and floured muffin tins at 325° until light brown.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut up dates into small pieces.
Put dates and shortening into large bowl and pour boiling water over them.
Let mixture sit for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix just until blended. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done in 2 greased loaf pans. After baking, cool on wire rack.

title: castillion style spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Mix. Pour into greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Test middle by piercing with butter knife.
If knife comes up clean, the corn bread is done.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs, blending.
Stir in milk.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in 325° oven for about an hour or until done.

title: double delicious bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass dish).
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over graham crumbs.
Sprinkle chips over mixture.
Press gently in pan. Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: choose-a-fruit syrup
directions: In a saucepan combine juice, sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon . Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook two minutes.
Stir in fruit. Heat through.
Serve warm.
Chill leftover syrup, covered up to three days.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dog biscuits
directions: In medium bowl, combine flours, milk powder, rolled oats, sugar and cornmeal.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in egg.
Stir instant bouillon granules into the hot water until dissolved.
Pour it slowly into the flour mixture, stirring with a fork to moisten.
Form dough into a ball and knead on floured board 5 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs.
Mix flour with soda and salt.
Blend in shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts. Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: maple cream coffee treats
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Separate biscuits dough into 20 four-inch circles.
Spoon 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture onto center of each biscuit.
Overlap dough over filling forming finger shaped rolls.
Place rolls seam side down in rows of 10 over syrup mixture in pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate or waxed paper.

title: topping for jello
directions: Cook flour, sugar, egg and pineapple juice until thick.
Add butter; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over jello.

title: quick and easy summer chicken(low-fat)
directions: Place skinned chicken in a large pan.
Add water and cook a few minutes.
Add rice and cover; cook on low for 2 to 3 minutes. Add chopped onions and peppers.
Cook a few minutes; then add chopped tomatoes and spices.
I use salt, pepper, minced garlic and soul food spices.
A great, quick, one-pot meal.
A good way to make use of your extra peppers and tomatoes.
You may need to add a little water.

title: potato soup(crock-pot)
directions: Put all above in crock-pot on low; let cook for 10 to 12 hours.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Melt butter and 3/4 cup brown sugar.
Add applesauce and heat thoroughly.
Place fruit into baking dish and spread butter mixture over fruit.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 15.

title: mexican taco stack
directions: Start layering with 1 tortilla, topped with beans, then tortilla, meat mixture, tortilla, onion and cheese, tortilla, olives and peppers, possibly cheese, tortilla, beans, tortilla, meat, etc.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cut in thin pie wedges and serve.

title: red hot pickle ring
directions: Peel, slice and core large cucumbers 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick (2 gallons cucumbers).
Soak in lime water 24 hours (2 cups lime to 8 1/2 cups water).
Drain and wash thoroughly.
Cover with 1 cup white vinegar, alum, food coloring and enough water to cover. Simmer 2 hours; drain well.

title: bread rolls
directions: Cut crusts off slices of bread. Butter each slice lightly. Spread with bacon cheese spread. Roll up and place close together on a cookie sheet. Drizzle with melted butter and broil.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, apples and raisins in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon over carrot mixture and toss.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 6 servings.
Counts as 1 vegetable and 1 fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well, except for broccoli.
Pour in casserole and top with frozen broccoli that is cooked and drained.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add buttermilk, flour, coconut, sugar, peaches and vanilla.
Beat eggs and mix everything together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: geelrys (yellow rice and raisins)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add rice.
Stir rice to coat with butter (do not brown).
Add water, cinnamon, salt and turmeric. Bring rice mixture to boil; cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Discard cinnamon.
Stir in raisins and heat for 1 more minute.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until very creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time; beating well after each egg. Add vanilla and almond and mix well.
Alternate flour and milk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in half of the cherries. Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven; set temperature at 275° and bake for 2 hours and 10 minutes. Cool thoroughly and frost.

title: tuna melt surprise
directions: Drain pineapple well; reserve 1 teaspoon juice.
In a small bowl, mix the reserved juice, salad dressing and mustard.
Stir together drained pineapple, tuna and celery in separate bowl; add salad dressing mix and mix well.
Arrange the toasted English muffins in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top each muffin half with equal amounts of tuna mixture.

Cut the cheese slices in half diagonally and place 1 triangle of cheese on each muffin half. Microwave, uncovered, on High (100% power) for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted, rotating the dish a half-turn once during cooking time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie crust.

title: "philly" 3-step mocha cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with mixer.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in chocolate and coffee.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set; cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fresh fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cover; chill 2 hours before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: mama strain's hot rolls
directions: Scald milk; pour over sugar, salt and shortening in large bowl.
Stir well; allow to cool until lukewarm.
Crumble yeast into lukewarm water.
Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Add yeast to lukewarm milk.
Add 3 1/2 cups sifted flour.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Gradually add remaining 3 cups flour.
Stir until all flour is added.
Brush top of mixture lightly with melted shortening.
Cover and set in warm place.
Allow dough to rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Place dough on lightly floured bread board and shape into a round ball.
Allow to stand 10 minutes or until double in bulk.
Pinch off individual rolls and place in pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in a moderate oven (375°).

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: Take your favorite potato salad recipe and substitute steamed cauliflower.
It is different and delicious.

title: popsicle
directions: Mix jello, Kool-Aid, sugar and hot water and shake to mix. Add cold water and pour into ice tubs and freeze.
Makes 20 nice textured circles and will not drip while being eaten.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in 3 tablespoons bacon grease. Combine rest of ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients except 1/2 c. cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55-60 min. or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 3-5 min. or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 min.

title: pumpernickel party platter
directions: Cook spinach and drain very well.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and vegetable soup mix.
Add spinach and blend well. Chill this mixture for a few hours.
Cut out center of round pumpernickel loaf.
Fill center with chilled dip.
Cut up removed bread and arrange on tray, surrounding filled loaf.
Further garnish tray with raw, sliced carrots for beautiful color and dipping.

title: fish quiche
directions: Prebake pie shell 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix together tuna (flaked), cheese and onions.
Beat eggs; mix in mayonnaise and 1/2 cup milk.

Pour over fish mixture that has been put in pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then finish baking at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before cutting to serve.
Cut in wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients (except butter and 1/2 of saltines) and pour into well-greased baking dish.
Combine 1/2 saltines and butter (melted); sprinkle evenly over casserole of corn mixture. Bake uncovered about 40 minutes until nicely brown.
When removed from oven, sprinkle lightly over top with paprika.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Early in day:
Start heating oven to 350°.
Grease well, then flour 10-inch heavy cast aluminum Bundt cake pan.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, cream oil and sugar until well mixed, then beat in egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Now beat in hot water.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves; beat into egg mixture.

title: chocolate dream(this is a good low-fat diabetic recipe)
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box, using skim milk.
Blend in entire container of Cool Whip.
In container of your choice (needs to be deep), begin layering pudding mixture and graham crackers alternately.
