(For best results, start with a layer of graham crackers on bottom.) Continue layers, leaving room for a layer of frosting on top.

title: italian steak rolls
directions: Brown cubed steaks.
Mix sausage, onion and cheese.
Spread mixture over each steak.
Roll each steak and secure with string. Place in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Before baking, pour spaghetti sauce over steak rolls.
Serve with spaghetti noodles.

title: double mocha cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to creamed mixture and beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in coffee and vanilla.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form, then gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out dry.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove layers from pans and cool completely.
Frost with Creamy Mocha Frosting.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over rest of ingredients.
Bake in a buttered dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water. Drain well.
Mash until smooth.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt, pepper and oleo. Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Place in refrigerator. Cool and cover.
Can store 2 weeks.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt butter. Add graham crackers and blend together. Press in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.

title: roll out cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients all together.
Blend butter with pastry cutter or fork into dry ingredients until fine particles. Add rest of ingredients.
Blend well.
Chill overnight or for a few hours.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick to 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.
I use any powdered sugar frosting.

title: brenda's cole slaw
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper together and pour over first 6 ingredients mixed together.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water or pineapple juice and water.
Let set slightly. Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate truffettes
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in large saucepan and bring to boil over low heat.
Simmer 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and whisk in cocoa, oatmeal, 1 cup nuts and vanilla.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls and roll in remaining nuts.
Refrigerate in covered container.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt. Shape into balls. Broil until brown, turn once. Drain grease. In separate pan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over meatballs and cover. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll steak in seasoned flour.
Brown onions slightly in melted shortening.
Remove onions.
Sear meat on both sides without browning and put in greased casserole.
Place onions, rice and tomatoes on top of meat.
Add remainder of flour mixture to shortening in skillet and blend until smooth.
Add water to mixture, stirring until smooth. Strain over meat in casserole.
Cook, covered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel delight
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and nuts.
Stir in melted butter.
Spread in a thin layer over a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool and then crumble.
Put half of the crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon caramel topping over crumbs.
Slice softened ice cream over topping.
Top with remaining crumbs and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip and chill.

title: dressing
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Combine everything in a large bowl.
Add a little water, if necessary, to give mixture a soupy consistency.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: hoppin john
directions: Cook pepper and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 3/4 of the cheese and the remaining ingredients.
Turn into a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Top with remaining cheese.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: artichoke oyster soup
directions: Cook until wilted, then add 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook until golden.
Add 1 can chicken broth and 1 can of either cream of mushroom or cream of celery soup.
Add 3 cans water (depending on preference of thick or thin soup), the 2 cans of artichoke hearts and fresh artichokes.
Cook about 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add oysters with juice during the last 5 or 10 minutes of cooking.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix with browned onion and celery.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, soup and water; mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Mix dressings and seasonings in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Refrigerate.

title: lamoyne's chicken
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon.
Line pan with dried beef.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: marinade (london broil)
directions: Put all ingredients together in a blender long enough to grind all.
Marinate meat for approximately 4 hours before broiling.

title: stuffing chicken
directions: Layer chicken in a greased baking dish.
Place next 3 ingredients layered on chicken.
Mix bouillon cubes with hot water and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nicole romo's chocolate cookie recipe(her very own)
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside. Combine cocoa, flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir together, slowly adding chocolate chips and Cocoa Krispies.

title: wild brown rice and chicken salad
directions: Cook rice accordingly (omit all butter); set aside.
Put warm chicken in medium bowl, pour over broth and lemon juice, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In large bowl, mix together pickled pepper and celery.
Add green onions and rice, stirring softly.
Add chicken with juice and broth.
Finally add nuts and green peas; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Serve on dark green lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, ginger, mace, soda and cloves.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together; set aside to cool. Beat in sugar until smooth.
Add flour, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly blended.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creamed lima beans
directions: Cook limas in water to cover and cook until beans test tender. Drain off almost all of the water and add salt, sugar, butter, margarine and half and half.
Reheat to cooking stage and stir in flour thickening using amount needed for desired thickness.
Add the sugar and salt after the beans are cooked to the tender stage or they tend to be tough.

title: shrimp wiggle
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Melt butter, blend in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick and smooth.
Heat. Serve in potty shelves, toast cups or on toast.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Makes 1 gallon (45 three-ounce drinks).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook
vermicelli;
drain.
Brown
sausage,
onion
and pepperoni; drain.
Mix vermicelli and margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking
dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the sauce, 1/2 meat mixture and
1/2 cheese.
Pour mushrooms over this and add the spices evenly.
Layer again with sauce, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Mix sugar and Rice Krispies together well.
Melt peanut butter and oleo together and pour over sugar and Krispies.
Mix real well. Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.
Melt morsels and paraffin together.
Cut candy into small pieces and use toothpicks to dip into morsels and paraffin.
Place on buttered wax paper until cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and pour 1/2 cup of water over apples.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon (you may wish to add a little sugar to apples if they are sour). Mix together 1 cup sugar, 3/4 cup flour and butter.
Blend until crumbly.
Add pecans and spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: sausage stew
directions: Cook sausage little more than half way.
Put a little water in another pot and add tomatoes; fill can with water and add.
Add bones to flavor.
Chop onions, pepper and garlic and add to sauce with diced potatoes and peas.
Put over medium heat and add sugar. Cut sausage to bite-size pieces and add to sauce.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours and serve.

title: hot dog chilli
directions: In a large pot cook hamburger with water until done.
Stir often.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Simmer, stirring often.

title: plantation pralines
directions: In a large kettle, combine sugar, baking soda, buttermilk and salt.
(If using candy thermometer, set in place).
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes or 210°, being sure to stir frequently and to scrape bottoms and sides.
Add butter and pecans.

title: poached salmon
directions: Remove head and tail.
Reserve, if you wish, for garnishing serving platter.
Place fish in a fish poacher or other deep baking pan.
Cover with water; remove fish.
Measure water in pan, then add bouillon and 1/8 cup vinegar for each quart of water in pan.
Add peppercorns and dill.
Bring to boil.
Add fish back to pan.
Cover; barely simmer until tender and flaky (should be less than 1 hour).
Arrange on platter of lettuce and replace head and tail.
Garnish as you wish.
Serve with your favorite fish sauce, such as dill sauce or a mustard sauce with chopped capers.
Try sour cream with mayo and white wine, seasoned with dill, pepper, garlic, etc.
Experiment!

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top chicken with cheese slices; combine soup and wine and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve with plain rice or rice to which you add mushrooms or water chestnuts.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake in three layers, but decrease water by 1/4 cup.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix, adding chips and nuts last.
Spread in two 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake 30 minuets at 350°.
Do not overcook!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, cream and powdered sugar and spread on bottom of pie crust.
Reserve 20 large berries.
Heat remaining berries over low heat.
When the berries start to boil, add sugar and cornstarch and cook until clear.
Cool.
Pour over the cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.
Use the 20 large berries to decorate top of pie.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: broccoli bake casserole
directions: Drain broccoli in colander overnight.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat the mushroom soup until creamy and smooth.
Spread over broccoli, then spread cheese over top.
Then sprinkle with bacon bits or onion rings.
You can also use 1 cup Bisquick; mix with 1/2 stick butter until it forms crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: maple crunch cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Put in the middle
of
the
dry
ingredients, the oil, egg yolks, water, flavoring, etc.
Beat until smooth.
Measure egg whites and cream of	tartar in bowl and beat until very stiff.
Fold batter into whites
of	eggs.
Fold
in nuts last.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 325°.
Turn upside down to cool.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla, and Cool Whip well. Tear up angel food cake in small pieces.
Crush Butterfinger bars into small pieces.
Make cake by layering angel food cake pieces, then Cool Whip mixture, and then Butterfinger pieces.
Repeat steps for next layer.

title: scaloppine la marsala
directions: Brown beef/turkey with onion until crumbly; drain any fat. Add garlic salt, tomato sauce and olives, stirring well; set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix sour cream, cottage cheese and chiles; set aside.
Grate the cheese; set aside.
Reserve 6 to 8 whole tortilla chips for garnish and coarsely crush the remainder in the bag.
Layer in a buttered large casserole dish:
1/2 of the crushed chips, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 sour cream mix and 1/2 grated cheese.
Repeat these layers, ending with the grated cheese and whole tortilla chips for garnish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Absolutely yummy!

title: never fail fudge
directions: Boil 5 minutes sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Pour over chocolate chips, Hershey bar, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix until creamy.
Pour into greased pan or cookie sheet.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the Ritz crackers and butter. Put in a casserole dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Crush the crackers and mix the butter into the crumbs. Spread on top of the veggie mixture. Put in preheated 350° oven and bake about 30 minutes, until lightly browned on top.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: homemade soap
directions: Strict is my diet.
I must not want.
It maketh me to lie down at night hungry.
It leadeth me past Baskin-Robbins.
It trieth my will power.
It leadeth me in the paths of starvation for my figure's sake.
Yea, though I walk through the aisles of the pastry department, I will buy no sweet rolls for they are fattening.
The cakes and the pies, they tempt me.
Before me is a table with celery and lettuce; my day's quota runneth over. Surely calories and weight charts shall follow me all the days of my life, and I shall dwell in fear of the scales forever.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwaveable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir chocolate until it is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 servings.

title: turkey-in-a-sack
directions: Select turkey carefully.
It should not exceed 14 to 20 pounds.
Wash and dry.
Combine pepper, salt, paprika and hot water.
Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Add peanut oil and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle Worcestershire powder over turkey.
Rub peanut oil mixture inside and outside of turkey.
Truss as desired.
Pour remaining oil and additional oil into large paper sack (type used in your grocery store, large, heavy-duty type with no holes).
Rub oil into inside of sack until every pore in every inch of the sack is sealed with oil mixture.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and beat well.
Pour into hot, greased iron skillet (use square one for lots of crust).
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together well and set aside.

title: sugarless spice cake(for diabetics)
directions: In a saucepan, cook raisins in water until water evaporates. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Stir in cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Add grated squash, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Blend together and pour into two greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together; chill until ready to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello, adding 1 cup boiling water only.
Grind oranges; add all ingredients and chill.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm; add sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, soda, egg and yeast mixture. Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition.
Part of the flour can be mixed in using the mixer at medium speed.
Cover and let rise in warm place until light and doubled, about 1 hour.
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Let rise again until light, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: lentil and sausage soup
directions: Rinse lentils and drain.
In a large saucepan, combine lentils, water, onion, bouillon granules, salt, basil and pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes. Quarter sausage lengthwise and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Add along with frozen broccoli and carrot.
Return to boiling.
Simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until lentils and vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: simply delicious
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts and spread in pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool!

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa and Coke in pan and add marshmallows to melt. Mix soda and milk in separate bowl; set aside.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, eggs and milk in mixer.
Add Coke mix and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost.

title: chili
directions: Cook onions in small amount of water in a large saucepan. When the onions are cooked dry, begin adding ground beef.

The more the mixture is stirred, the finer the texture of the chili. Add salt, pepper, paprika and chili powder according to taste. When beef is well cooked, add tomato paste and tomato soup. Simmer on low heat about 30 minutes; stir often.

title: quick minestrone soup
directions: Heat vegetable oil in large pan.
Add onion and garlic; heat 2 minutes.
Stir in vegetable juice; bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mixed vegetables, pasta and spinach.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: one, two, three, four
directions: Mix together all but filling.
Reserve 1/4 cup batter. Spread on large cookie sheet.
Cover with pie filling.
Drop remaining batter on top and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugarless banana nut loaf
directions: Beat together shortening, Sweet 'N Low, eggs and milk.
Add bananas, nuts, soda, flour and vanilla.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granny's hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Puppies will float when done.

title: anise cheese cake
directions: Beat Ricotta, eggs and sugar first, then add anise flavoring, lemon juice, milk and baking powder.
Mix well.
Melt butter and pour in bottom of baking pan.
Pour everything into pan.
Sprinkle candy over it.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: deluxe sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, confectioners sugar, egg, vanilla, and almond extract. Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar. Cover, chill 2 to 3 hours. Heat oven to 375°.

Divide dough in half. Roll each half 3/16 inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board, cut into desired shapes; Sprinkle with granulated sugar. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 7 - 8 minutes or until brown on edge.

title: oatmeal nut cookies
directions: Put flour into a 10-inch skillet.
Stir to light golden brown; add oatmeal.
Stir until slightly toasted color.
In a bowl, beat egg until fairly thick.
Add sugar and beat until very thick. Fold in nuts, flour and oatmeal.
Drop on greased cookie sheet 1 level tablespoon of mixture and flatten with hand.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: sparkling red punch
directions: Mix red punch and frozen lemonade; chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Prepare at least 2 cups per person because everyone really enjoys this punch.

title: delicious fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese. sour cream, sugars, and syrup or vanilla; beat smooth. Chill and serve with fruit.

title: chicken marinade for grill
directions: Mix all and marinate overnight.
Continue to brush on marinade while cooking on the grill.

title: peaches n' cream
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder, pudding, butter, egg and milk. Beat for 2 minutes, medium speed.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan. Place sliced peaches over batter.
Combine in a small bowl the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved juice; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon to within 1-inch of dish edge.
Combine and sprinkle over cheese filling 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 8.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Heat soup, sugar, oil and vinegar and pour over vegetables.

title: becky's banana bread
directions: Mix together first seven ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Flour pan and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandma's chicken and dumpling soup
directions: Place fryer, water, bouillon, peppercorns and cloves in kettle and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until chicken is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Cool chicken just slightly; cut into bite-size pieces and set aside.
Strain and skim chicken broth. Put reserved chicken and broth in large kettle.
Add cans of broth, soups, celery, carrots, onion, potatoes, bay leaf, peas and seasoned salt.
Put cover on kettle.
Simmer soup in low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
About 30 minutes before serving, make dumplings by sifting flour, salt, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon pepper together.
Add 1 well beaten egg, 2 tablespoons melted butter and enough milk to make moist, stiff batter.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling liquid.
Cook covered for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: chili cheese pie
directions: Prick and bake pie crust at 400 degrees for 10 minutes. Sprinkle cheese into bottom of crust; then top evenly with green chilies.
Combine eggs, sour cream, and onion salt; then pour evenly over chilies.
Sprinkle rotel around the inside rim of pie crust.
Bake for 25 minutes and serve hot.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in saucepan.
Blend in milk.
Mix well until smooth.
Add water.
Stir well.
Bring to boil for 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello
with
hot water; add blueberries and pineapple. Congeal until firm.

title: lemon delight pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and lightly flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Prick deeply every inch with long-tined fork.
Spoon half of glaze over hot cake in pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spoon remaining glaze over cake.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Mix and boil the sugar and milk for about 5 minutes.
Pour over cake as soon as it is done, while still hot.
When cake is cool, put Cool Whip over it and sprinkle with coconut.

title: honey cake squares
directions: Combine walnuts and dates; dredge in 3 tablespoons flour, stirring to coat evenly.
Set aside.
Cream butter in a large bowl. Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine 1 cup flour and next 4 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition.
Stir in the walnut-date mixture.
Spoon mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Drizzle with honey; cool in pan.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares or diamonds.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yields 4 dozen.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Brown bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble.
Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook all day.
Makes 10 servings.
(Optional: Bake in oven for 1 hour.)

title: pasta with fresh tomatoes, basil and parmesan
directions: Cook pasta until very al dente.
Drain and toss with olive oil and lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature and toss to coat thoroughly.
Add basil, tomatoes, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with basil leaves.
Tastes best when made on the day to be served.
Serves 8 to 10 as a salad.

title: dirt cake
directions: Will also need 1 glass bowl or medium size flowerpot.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix well over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
When bread is done, poke holes in bread and brush glaze on top of bread. Freezes well.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Rinse, pat dry and halve mushrooms, place in a large bowl. In a saucepan, combine oil, vinegar, water, onion, garlic, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour hot marinade over mushrooms.
Stir in olives and their liquid, mix well and pack in quart jar.
Refrigerate at least 2 days.

title: easy white fudge
directions: Mix butter, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.

title: crawfish or shrimp chowder
directions: Saute crawfish tails, oleo, and green onions. In large pot combine cream cheese, cream of potato soup, cream of mushroom soup, corn, half and half, red peppers, salt and pepper. Add crawfish tails mixture and heat until hot. Serve with crackers. Makes one large pot.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand a while before serving.

title: tortilla ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion, peppers, mayo & ham. Spread mixture on tortillas up to about 1 inch from top.
Starting from bottom, roll tortilla up, mixture will squeeze to top when rolling.
Roll each into individual pieces of saran wrap. Refrigerate 3 hours and slice up.

title: cherry o cheese refrigerator pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until softened and then add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Whip or mix until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate until mixture is firm, then add your cherry pie filling to the top.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: egg casserole
directions: Break eggs into buttered baking dish; do not stir.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour evaporated milk over eggs; cover with grated cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°
for about 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.
You might want to add 1 tablespoon finely chopped bell pepper, parsley or minced onions.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg, then add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful in hot oil.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes on low to medium heat.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
May substitute corn for apples.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and cube into 1/2 inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients except apples and nuts in large bowl using mixer. Fold in apples and nuts with a spoon.
Pour in a greased bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour.
Cool in pan before dumping.

title: noodles with veal sauce
directions: Cube veal.
In a large skillet cook veal in oil.
Slice onions into rings.
Add celery and onions to veal.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, sugar, paprika and salt. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook noodles and drain.
Spoon veal mixture over noodles.

title: green beans with garlic(8 servings)
directions: Wash beans.
Remove ends and slice beans.
Place beans in 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water).
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Boil uncovered 5 minutes.
Cover and boil until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Return beans to saucepan. Add butter, garlic, thyme, lemon juice and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, just until butter melts and beans are hot, 1 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: beetroot pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Drain, reserving half pint of the liquid.
Slip skins and slice when cool.
Add the next 4 ingredients to the reserved beet juice and boil up again.
Slice onions thinly and layer them in jars with the beets.
Pour hot vinegar juice over the onions and beets and seal jars tightly. Let set for a week in a cool place.

title: dandelion and lettuce salad
directions: Cut lettuce, greens, onions, green pepper and Swiss cheese into small pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, tossing lightly.
Add olive oil and vinegar, toss lightly.
Gently mix in the tomatoes and eggs or leave on top.

title: raw cranberry relish
directions: Wash and sort fruit; do not peel.
Grind in food processor or blender.
Stir in sugar.
Marinate 24 hours.
Makes 1 quart. Store 1 month.
Add gelatin and mold, if desired.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Chill milk until ice cold.
Chill and drain peaches, save syrup.
Set aside 10 slices for top and dice remaining peaches. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of peach syrup, then blend in softened cheese and sugar.
Whip chilled milk in chilled bowl until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and whip until stiff.
Beat in cheese mix 1/4 at a time.
Mix will be thin.
Fold into drained diced peaches.
Turn into chilled pie crust and top with remaining peach slices.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine ingredients; beat until blended completely.
Pour in angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain; spread in bottom of 9x13 pan. Sprinkle soup mix over ground beef.
Layer with mushroom soup, then frozen vegetables, celery soup and top with tater tots in rows.
Cover with foil; uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients, then pour over cucumbers in gallon jug. Store in refrigerator until all eaten.
Shake twice a day.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and add bacon drippings.
Add soup, mayo, egg, onion and spices; mix together. Place grated cheese on top of casserole and put crumbled crackers on top of cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Chill.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine tomatoes, garlic, lemon juice, parsley, chives, tomato juice and olive oil.
Puree in an electric blender.
Add green peppers, onions and cucumber.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with small bowls of croutons, chives, onions, peppers and cucumbers for garnishing.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add enough water to juice to make a cup.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve Jell-O.
Add fruit, buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar with corn meal and flour.
Add melted margarine, lemon juice and rind.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until tested done.
Do not overbake.
Bake approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Simmer to thick consistency before putting rellenos in oven.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all together and put margarine on top.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add next 4 ingredients. Mix well.
Makes a very stiff dough.
Put 3/4 of mixture in a 10 x 15-inch pan and press down firmly to cover bottom of pan.

title: strufalie(italian christmas balls)
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; cut in butter.
Set aside.
Beat eggs with apple cider.
On board, make a well in the flour mixture.
Pour in egg mixture and mix until soft dough.
Do not knead too much, just bring together.
Let rest 1 hour.
Roll into ropes.
Cut off 1/2-inch pieces and deep fry in 400° oil.
I use the electric frypan and about 2-inches of oil.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add soups and chicken broth, green chilies and chicken pieces.
Put into 2-quart baking dish.
Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.
Loaf pan, approximately 30 minutes.
Cake pan, approximately 15 minutes.

title: mapley nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and granulated sugar in a bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press into bottom of a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Beat egg, brown sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla in a bowl until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over warm crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is firm around edges but slightly soft in middle.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook on high until hot.
Turn down to low and cook 8 to 10 hours or overnight with lid on.
Take lid off and cook until thick, about 2 hours.
Makes 2 quarts and 1 pint, with a little left over.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to bake at 400°. Brown beef in skillet and drain. Combine all dry ingredients (baking soda, salt, corn meal).
Beat eggs.

title: schnecker
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add flour and salt gradually into butter mixture.
Knead into ball. Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick; cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Spread each square with raspberry jam, apricot jam, etc., to within 1/4 inch of edges.
Roll up firmly; place rolled edge down on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Stir together egg yolks and 3/4 cup sugar.
Melt 2 cups milk, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon Crisco.
In a separate glass cup, crumble 2 yeast cakes into 1/2 cup lukewarm milk (80°) and 1/2 teaspoon sugar; let stand 5 minutes.
Add milk to egg mix. Add yeast mixture.
Combine with flour; add gradually until you reach a good dough consistency.
Let raise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Repeat.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and put in crock-pot.
Saute onion and green pepper and add to ground beef.
Add peppers, cheese and soups.
Cook in crock-pot, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts.
Dip with 100% white restaurant corn chips.

title: christmas sandies
directions: Cream together margarine and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Then add flour and mix well.
Add pecans and form small balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until delicately brown.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Combine sausage, potatoes and melted margarine.
Sprinkle onion soup mix onto potato mixture.
Stir until potatoes and sausage are coated with onion soup.
Cover and bake in 375° oven until potatoes are tender or meat and potatoes are slightly brown.

title: pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, tomatoes, cabbage, green peppers, onions and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Boil remaining ingredients.
Drain cucumber mixture good.
Then add to syrup.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: chick-a-biddy casserole
directions: Grease a large baking dish.
Spread rice evenly in bottom and then shake onion soup mix over rice.
Remove skin from chicken and place chicken on top of rice and onion soup mix.
Slowly combine boiling water with can of chicken soup and pour over chicken, rice and onion soup mix.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°. Uncover for the last 1/2 hour.

title: pancakes(yield: 10 medium pancakes)
directions: 1. Mix milk, egg and vanilla together.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Yields about 7 dozen appetizers, depending on size.

title: marinated mushrooms(short cut)
directions: Place mushrooms in large, glass container.
Pour entire bottle of dressing over mushrooms so they are totally covered. Refrigerate overnight.

title: gingerbread syrup
directions: Combine ingredients and bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour 1/2 flour in liquid and mix; keep adding flour until forms a ball.
Knead.
Grease pan and bowl.
Let set 2 hours. Roll in little balls and drop in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Lay the sliced steak between sheets of waxed paper.
Season with salt and pepper; roll up and set aside for 2 hours at room temperature.
In a saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring, for 15 seconds.
Add mustard and broth; stir until thickened and set aside.

title: spinach salad
directions: Use half lettuce and half spinach.
Layer with remaining ingredients.
Serve with your choice of dressing.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini; cook until tender in boiling salted water. Drain well and put in greased casserole dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter; add 3 tablespoons flour.
Stir until blended.
Peel and chop 3 large tomatoes or 2 cups canned (drained).
Cut green pepper and onion.
Add vegetables to butter mixture with salt, brown sugar and oregano.
Cook 5 minutes or more.
Cover zucchini with grated cheese, then pour vegetable mixture over.
Cover with another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: orange whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
When thoroughly mixed, add the Cool Whip.
Chill well.

title: german chocolate cake with coconut pecan frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks one at a time; beat after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in three 9-inch cake pans lined on bottom with paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; cool.
Frost tops only with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: grandma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Put in greased baking dish.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Mix in a large bowl. Drop by spoon to form biscuits.
Bake at 375° or 400°. Dough can be kept a week in refrigerator, covered.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt together. In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla with wooden spoon. Beat in eggs. Gradually add dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Pour melted margarine in greased casserole dish.
Place potato chunks
in dish and stir until chunks are coated.
Now sprinkle garlic salt (to taste) on potatoes and Mrs.
Dash, as well.
Bake in oven about 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Stir and resprinkle spices halfway through baking.
May microwave potatoes also until done; be sure to add more spices and stir halfway through cooking time, about 20 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown stuffing in skillet. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: helen's chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in greased pan.
Place ingredients on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo syrup, melted butter, pecans and vanilla flavoring.
Combine all together and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
